164bool isBackForwardLoadType(FrameLoadType type)
165{
166 switch (type) {
167 case FrameLoadType::Standard:
168 case FrameLoadType::Reload:
169 case FrameLoadType::ReloadFromOrigin:
170 case FrameLoadType::ReloadExpiredOnly:
171 case FrameLoadType::Same:
172 case FrameLoadType::RedirectWithLockedBackForwardList:
173 case FrameLoadType::Replace:
174 return false;
175 case FrameLoadType::Back:
176 case FrameLoadType::Forward:
177 case FrameLoadType::IndexedBackForward:
178 return true;
179 }
180 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
181 return false;
182}
183
184bool isReload(FrameLoadType type)
185{
186 switch (type) {
187 case FrameLoadType::Reload:
188 case FrameLoadType::ReloadFromOrigin:
189 case FrameLoadType::ReloadExpiredOnly:
190 return true;
191 case FrameLoadType::Standard:
192 case FrameLoadType::Same:
193 case FrameLoadType::RedirectWithLockedBackForwardList:
194 case FrameLoadType::Replace:
195 case FrameLoadType::Back:
196 case FrameLoadType::Forward:
197 case FrameLoadType::IndexedBackForward:
198 return false;
199 }
200 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
201 return false;
202}

204// This is not in the FrameLoader class to emphasize that it does not depend on
205// private FrameLoader data, and to avoid increasing the number of public functions
206// with access to private data. Since only this .cpp file needs it, making it
207// non-member lets us exclude it from the header file, thus keeping FrameLoader.h's
208// API simpler.
209//
210static bool isDocumentSandboxed(Frame& frame, SandboxFlags mask)
211{
212 return frame.document() && frame.document()->isSandboxed(mask);
213}

215class PageLevelForbidScope {
216protected:
217 explicit PageLevelForbidScope(Page* page)
218 : m_page(makeWeakPtr(page))
219 {
220 }
221
222 ~PageLevelForbidScope() = default;
223
224 WeakPtr<Page> m_page;
225};
226
227struct ForbidPromptsScope : public PageLevelForbidScope {
228 explicit ForbidPromptsScope(Page* page)
229 : PageLevelForbidScope(page)
230 {
231 if (m_page)
232 m_page->forbidPrompts();
233 }
234
235 ~ForbidPromptsScope()
236 {
237 if (m_page)
238 m_page->allowPrompts();
239 }
240};
241
242struct ForbidSynchronousLoadsScope : public PageLevelForbidScope {
243 explicit ForbidSynchronousLoadsScope(Page* page)
244 : PageLevelForbidScope(page)
245 {
246 if (m_page)
247 m_page->forbidSynchronousLoads();
248 }
249
250 ~ForbidSynchronousLoadsScope()
251 {
252 if (m_page)
253 m_page->allowSynchronousLoads();
254 }

257class FrameLoader::FrameProgressTracker {
258 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
259public:
260 explicit FrameProgressTracker(Frame& frame)
261 : m_frame(frame)
262 , m_inProgress(false)
263 {
264 }
265
266 ~FrameProgressTracker()
267 {
268 if (m_inProgress && m_frame.page())
269 m_frame.page()->progress().progressCompleted(m_frame);
270 }
271
272 void progressStarted()
273 {
274 ASSERT(m_frame.page());
275 if (!m_inProgress)
276 m_frame.page()->progress().progressStarted(m_frame);
277 m_inProgress = true;
278 }
279
280 void progressCompleted()
281 {
282 ASSERT(m_inProgress);
283 ASSERT(m_frame.page());
284 m_inProgress = false;
285 m_frame.page()->progress().progressCompleted(m_frame);
286 platformStrategies()->loaderStrategy()->pageLoadCompleted(*m_frame.page());
287 }
288
289private:
290 Frame& m_frame;
291 bool m_inProgress;
292};

338void FrameLoader::init()
339{
340 // This somewhat odd set of steps gives the frame an initial empty document.
341 setPolicyDocumentLoader(m_client->createDocumentLoader(ResourceRequest(URL({ }, emptyString())), SubstituteData()).ptr());
342 setProvisionalDocumentLoader(m_policyDocumentLoader.get());
343 m_provisionalDocumentLoader->startLoadingMainResource();
344
345 Ref<Frame> protect(m_frame);
346 m_frame.document()->cancelParsing();
347 m_stateMachine.advanceTo(FrameLoaderStateMachine::DisplayingInitialEmptyDocument);
348
349 m_networkingContext = m_client->createNetworkingContext();
350 m_progressTracker = makeUnique<FrameProgressTracker>(m_frame);
351}
352
353void FrameLoader::initForSynthesizedDocument(const URL&)
354{
355 // FIXME: We need to initialize the document URL to the specified URL. Currently the URL is empty and hence
356 // FrameLoader::checkCompleted() will overwrite the URL of the document to be activeDocumentLoader()->documentURL().
357
358 auto loader = m_client->createDocumentLoader(ResourceRequest(URL({ }, emptyString())), SubstituteData());
359 loader->attachToFrame(m_frame);
360 loader->setResponse(ResourceResponse(URL(), "text/html"_s, 0, String()));
361 loader->setCommitted(true);
362 setDocumentLoader(loader.ptr());
363
364 m_stateMachine.advanceTo(FrameLoaderStateMachine::DisplayingInitialEmptyDocument);
365 m_stateMachine.advanceTo(FrameLoaderStateMachine::DisplayingInitialEmptyDocumentPostCommit);
366 m_stateMachine.advanceTo(FrameLoaderStateMachine::CommittedFirstRealLoad);
367 m_client->transitionToCommittedForNewPage();
368
369 m_didCallImplicitClose = true;
370 m_isComplete = true;
371 m_state = FrameState::Complete;
372 m_needsClear = true;
373
374 m_networkingContext = m_client->createNetworkingContext();
375 m_progressTracker = makeUnique<FrameProgressTracker>(m_frame);
376}

398void FrameLoader::setDefersLoading(bool defers)
399{
400 if (m_documentLoader)
401 m_documentLoader->setDefersLoading(defers);
402 if (m_provisionalDocumentLoader)
403 m_provisionalDocumentLoader->setDefersLoading(defers);
404 if (m_policyDocumentLoader)
405 m_policyDocumentLoader->setDefersLoading(defers);
406 history().setDefersLoading(defers);
407
408 if (!defers) {
409 m_frame.navigationScheduler().startTimer();
410 startCheckCompleteTimer();
411 }

414void FrameLoader::checkContentPolicy(const ResourceResponse& response, PolicyCheckIdentifier identifier, ContentPolicyDecisionFunction&& function)
415{
416 if (!activeDocumentLoader()) {
417 // Load was cancelled
418 function(PolicyAction::Ignore, identifier);
419 return;
420 }
421
422 // FIXME: Validate the policy check identifier.
423 client().dispatchDecidePolicyForResponse(response, activeDocumentLoader()->request(), identifier, activeDocumentLoader()->downloadAttribute(), WTFMove(function));
424}

426void FrameLoader::changeLocation(const URL& url, const String& passedTarget, Event* triggeringEvent, const ReferrerPolicy& referrerPolicy, ShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy, std::optional<NewFrameOpenerPolicy> openerPolicy, const AtomString& downloadAttribute, const SystemPreviewInfo& systemPreviewInfo, std::optional<PrivateClickMeasurement>&& privateClickMeasurement)
427{
428 auto* frame = lexicalFrameFromCommonVM();
429 auto initiatedByMainFrame = frame && frame->isMainFrame() ? InitiatedByMainFrame::Yes : InitiatedByMainFrame::Unknown;
430
431 NewFrameOpenerPolicy newFrameOpenerPolicy = openerPolicy.value_or(referrerPolicy == ReferrerPolicy::NoReferrer ? NewFrameOpenerPolicy::Suppress : NewFrameOpenerPolicy::Allow);
432 FrameLoadRequest frameLoadRequest(*m_frame.document(), m_frame.document()->securityOrigin(), { url }, passedTarget, initiatedByMainFrame, downloadAttribute, systemPreviewInfo);
433 frameLoadRequest.setNewFrameOpenerPolicy(newFrameOpenerPolicy);
434 frameLoadRequest.setReferrerPolicy(referrerPolicy);
435 frameLoadRequest.setShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy(shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy);
436 frameLoadRequest.disableShouldReplaceDocumentIfJavaScriptURL();
437 changeLocation(WTFMove(frameLoadRequest), triggeringEvent, WTFMove(privateClickMeasurement));
438}
439
440void FrameLoader::changeLocation(FrameLoadRequest&& frameRequest, Event* triggeringEvent, std::optional<PrivateClickMeasurement>&& privateClickMeasurement)
441{
442 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "changeLocation: frame load started");
443 ASSERT(frameRequest.resourceRequest().httpMethod() == "GET");
444
445 Ref<Frame> protect(m_frame);
446
447 if (frameRequest.resourceRequest().url().protocolIsJavaScript()) {
448 m_frame.script().executeJavaScriptURL(frameRequest.resourceRequest().url(), &frameRequest.requester().securityOrigin(), frameRequest.shouldReplaceDocumentIfJavaScriptURL());
449 m_quickRedirectComing = false;
450 return;
451 }
452
453 if (frameRequest.frameName().isEmpty())
454 frameRequest.setFrameName(m_frame.document()->baseTarget());
455
456 m_frame.document()->contentSecurityPolicy()->upgradeInsecureRequestIfNeeded(frameRequest.resourceRequest(), ContentSecurityPolicy::InsecureRequestType::Navigation);
457
458 loadFrameRequest(WTFMove(frameRequest), triggeringEvent, { }, WTFMove(privateClickMeasurement));
459}

461void FrameLoader::submitForm(Ref<FormSubmission>&& submission)
462{
463 ASSERT(submission->method() == FormSubmission::Method::Post || submission->method() == FormSubmission::Method::Get);
464
465 // FIXME: Find a good spot for these.
466 ASSERT(!submission->state().sourceDocument().frame() || submission->state().sourceDocument().frame() == &m_frame);
467
468 if (!m_frame.page())
469 return;
470
471 if (submission->action().isEmpty())
472 return;
473
474 if (isDocumentSandboxed(m_frame, SandboxForms)) {
475 // FIXME: This message should be moved off the console once a solution to https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=103274 exists.
476 m_frame.document()->addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, "Blocked form submission to '" + submission->action().stringCenterEllipsizedToLength() + "' because the form's frame is sandboxed and the 'allow-forms' permission is not set.");
477 return;
478 }
479
480 URL formAction = submission->action();
481 if (!m_frame.document()->contentSecurityPolicy()->allowFormAction(formAction))
482 return;
483
484 if (formAction.protocolIsJavaScript()) {
485 m_isExecutingJavaScriptFormAction = true;
486 Ref<Frame> protect(m_frame);
487 m_frame.script().executeJavaScriptURL(submission->action(), nullptr, DoNotReplaceDocumentIfJavaScriptURL);
488 m_isExecutingJavaScriptFormAction = false;
489 return;
490 }
491
492 Frame* targetFrame = findFrameForNavigation(submission->target(), &submission->state().sourceDocument());
493 if (!targetFrame) {
494 if (!DOMWindow::allowPopUp(m_frame) && !UserGestureIndicator::processingUserGesture())
495 return;
496
497 // FIXME: targetFrame can be null for two distinct reasons:
498 // 1. The frame was not found by name, so we should try opening a new window.
499 // 2. The frame was found, but navigating it was not allowed, e.g. by HTML5 sandbox or by origin checks.
500 // Continuing form submission makes no sense in the latter case.
501 // There is a repeat check after timer fires, so this is not a correctness issue.
502
503 targetFrame = &m_frame;
504 } else
505 submission->clearTarget();
506
507 if (!targetFrame->page())
508 return;
509
510 if (m_frame.tree().isDescendantOf(targetFrame))
511 m_submittedFormURL = submission->requestURL();
512
513 submission->setReferrer(outgoingReferrer());
514 submission->setOrigin(SecurityPolicy::generateOriginHeader(m_frame.document()->referrerPolicy(), submission->requestURL(), m_frame.document()->securityOrigin()));
515
516 targetFrame->navigationScheduler().scheduleFormSubmission(WTFMove(submission));
517}

519void FrameLoader::stopLoading(UnloadEventPolicy unloadEventPolicy)
520{
521 if (m_frame.document() && m_frame.document()->parser())
522 m_frame.document()->parser()->stopParsing();
523
524 if (unloadEventPolicy != UnloadEventPolicy::None)
525 dispatchUnloadEvents(unloadEventPolicy);
526
527 m_isComplete = true; // to avoid calling completed() in finishedParsing()
528 m_didCallImplicitClose = true; // don't want that one either
529
530 if (m_frame.document() && m_frame.document()->parsing()) {
531 finishedParsing();
532 m_frame.document()->setParsing(false);
533 }
534
535 if (auto* document = m_frame.document()) {
536 // FIXME: Should the DatabaseManager watch for something like ActiveDOMObject::stop() rather than being special-cased here?
537 DatabaseManager::singleton().stopDatabases(*document, nullptr);
538 }
539
540 policyChecker().stopCheck();
541
542 // FIXME: This will cancel redirection timer, which really needs to be restarted when restoring the frame from b/f cache.
543 m_frame.navigationScheduler().cancel();
544}
545
546void FrameLoader::stop()
547{
548 // http://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=10854
549 // The frame's last ref may be removed and it will be deleted by checkCompleted().
550 Ref<Frame> protect(m_frame);
551
552 if (DocumentParser* parser = m_frame.document()->parser()) {
553 parser->stopParsing();
554 parser->finish();
555 }
556}
557
558void FrameLoader::closeURL()
559{
560 history().saveDocumentState();
561
562 RefPtr<Document> currentDocument = m_frame.document();
563 UnloadEventPolicy unloadEventPolicy;
564 if (m_frame.page() && m_frame.page()->chrome().client().isSVGImageChromeClient()) {
565 // If this is the SVGDocument of an SVGImage, no need to dispatch events or recalcStyle.
566 unloadEventPolicy = UnloadEventPolicy::None;
567 } else {
568 // Should only send the pagehide event here if the current document exists and has not been placed in the back/forward cache.
569 unloadEventPolicy = currentDocument && currentDocument->backForwardCacheState() == Document::NotInBackForwardCache ? UnloadEventPolicy::UnloadAndPageHide : UnloadEventPolicy::UnloadOnly;
570 }
571
572 stopLoading(unloadEventPolicy);
573
574 if (currentDocument)
575 currentDocument->editor().clearUndoRedoOperations();
576}
577
578bool FrameLoader::didOpenURL()
579{
580 if (m_frame.navigationScheduler().redirectScheduledDuringLoad()) {
581 // A redirect was scheduled before the document was created.
582 // This can happen when one frame changes another frame's location.
583 return false;
584 }
585
586 m_frame.navigationScheduler().cancel();
587
588 m_isComplete = false;
589 m_didCallImplicitClose = false;
590
591 // If we are still in the process of initializing an empty document then
592 // its frame is not in a consistent state for rendering, so avoid setJSStatusBarText
593 // since it may cause clients to attempt to render the frame.
594 if (!m_stateMachine.creatingInitialEmptyDocument()) {
595 DOMWindow* window = m_frame.document()->domWindow();
596 window->setStatus(String());
597 window->setDefaultStatus(String());
598 }
599
600 started();
601
602 return true;
603}
604
605void FrameLoader::didExplicitOpen()
606{
607 m_isComplete = false;
608 m_didCallImplicitClose = false;
609
610 // Calling document.open counts as committing the first real document load.
611 if (!m_stateMachine.committedFirstRealDocumentLoad())
612 m_stateMachine.advanceTo(FrameLoaderStateMachine::DisplayingInitialEmptyDocumentPostCommit);
613
614 if (auto* document = m_frame.document())
615 m_client->dispatchDidExplicitOpen(document->url(), document->contentType());
616
617 // Prevent window.open(url) -- eg window.open("about:blank") -- from blowing away results
618 // from a subsequent window.document.open / window.document.write call.
619 // Canceling redirection here works for all cases because document.open
620 // implicitly precedes document.write.
621 m_frame.navigationScheduler().cancel();
622}
623
624static inline bool shouldClearWindowName(const Frame& frame, const Document& newDocument)
625{
626 if (!frame.isMainFrame())
627 return false;
628
629 if (frame.loader().opener())
630 return false;
631
632 return !newDocument.securityOrigin().isSameOriginAs(frame.document()->securityOrigin());
633}
634
635void FrameLoader::clear(Document* newDocument, bool clearWindowProperties, bool clearScriptObjects, bool clearFrameView, WTF::Function<void()>&& handleDOMWindowCreation)
636{
637 bool neededClear = m_needsClear;
638 m_needsClear = false;
639
640 if (neededClear && m_frame.document()->backForwardCacheState() != Document::InBackForwardCache) {
641 m_frame.document()->cancelParsing();
642 m_frame.document()->stopActiveDOMObjects();
643 bool hadLivingRenderTree = m_frame.document()->hasLivingRenderTree();
644 m_frame.document()->willBeRemovedFromFrame();
645 if (hadLivingRenderTree)
646 m_frame.document()->adjustFocusedNodeOnNodeRemoval(*m_frame.document());
647 }
648
649 if (handleDOMWindowCreation)
650 handleDOMWindowCreation();
651
652 if (!neededClear)
653 return;
654
655 // Do this after detaching the document so that the unload event works.
656 if (clearWindowProperties) {
657 InspectorInstrumentation::frameWindowDiscarded(m_frame, m_frame.document()->domWindow());
658 m_frame.document()->domWindow()->resetUnlessSuspendedForDocumentSuspension();
659 m_frame.windowProxy().clearJSWindowProxiesNotMatchingDOMWindow(newDocument->domWindow(), m_frame.document()->backForwardCacheState() == Document::AboutToEnterBackForwardCache);
660
661 if (shouldClearWindowName(m_frame, *newDocument))
662 m_frame.tree().setName(nullAtom());
663 }
664
665 m_frame.eventHandler().clear();
666
667 if (clearFrameView && m_frame.view())
668 m_frame.view()->clear();
669
670 // Do not drop the document before the ScriptController and view are cleared
671 // as some destructors might still try to access the document.
672 m_frame.setDocument(nullptr);
673
674 subframeLoader().clear();
675
676 if (clearWindowProperties)
677 m_frame.windowProxy().setDOMWindow(newDocument->domWindow());
678
679 if (clearScriptObjects)
680 m_frame.script().clearScriptObjects();
681
682 m_frame.script().enableEval();
683
684 m_frame.navigationScheduler().clear();
685
686 m_checkTimer.stop();
687 m_shouldCallCheckCompleted = false;
688 m_shouldCallCheckLoadComplete = false;
689
690 if (m_stateMachine.isDisplayingInitialEmptyDocument() && m_stateMachine.committedFirstRealDocumentLoad())
691 m_stateMachine.advanceTo(FrameLoaderStateMachine::CommittedFirstRealLoad);
692}
693
694void FrameLoader::receivedFirstData()
695{
696 auto protectedFrame = makeRef(m_frame);
697
698 dispatchDidCommitLoad(std::nullopt, std::nullopt);
699 dispatchDidClearWindowObjectsInAllWorlds();
700 dispatchGlobalObjectAvailableInAllWorlds();
701
702 if (!m_documentLoader)
703 return;
704
705 auto& documentLoader = *m_documentLoader;
706 auto& title = documentLoader.title();
707 if (!title.string.isNull())
708 m_client->dispatchDidReceiveTitle(title);
709
710 ASSERT(m_frame.document());
711 auto& document = *m_frame.document();
712
713 LinkLoader::loadLinksFromHeader(documentLoader.response().httpHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::Link), document.url(), document, LinkLoader::MediaAttributeCheck::MediaAttributeEmpty);
714
715 scheduleRefreshIfNeeded(document, documentLoader.response().httpHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::Refresh));
716}
717
718void FrameLoader::setOutgoingReferrer(const URL& url)
719{
720 m_outgoingReferrer = url.strippedForUseAsReferrer();
721}
722
723void FrameLoader::didBeginDocument(bool dispatch)
724{
725 m_needsClear = true;
726 m_isComplete = false;
727 m_didCallImplicitClose = false;
728 m_frame.document()->setReadyState(Document::Loading);
729
730 if (m_pendingStateObject) {
731 m_frame.document()->statePopped(*m_pendingStateObject);
732 m_pendingStateObject = nullptr;
733 }
734
735 if (dispatch)
736 dispatchDidClearWindowObjectsInAllWorlds();
737
738 updateFirstPartyForCookies();
739 m_frame.document()->initContentSecurityPolicy();
740
741 const Settings& settings = m_frame.settings();
742 m_frame.document()->cachedResourceLoader().setImagesEnabled(settings.areImagesEnabled());
743 m_frame.document()->cachedResourceLoader().setAutoLoadImages(settings.loadsImagesAutomatically());
744
745 if (m_documentLoader) {
746 String dnsPrefetchControl = m_documentLoader->response().httpHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::XDNSPrefetchControl);
747 if (!dnsPrefetchControl.isEmpty())
748 m_frame.document()->parseDNSPrefetchControlHeader(dnsPrefetchControl);
749
750 m_frame.document()->contentSecurityPolicy()->didReceiveHeaders(ContentSecurityPolicyResponseHeaders(m_documentLoader->response()), referrer(), ContentSecurityPolicy::ReportParsingErrors::No);
751
752 String referrerPolicy = m_documentLoader->response().httpHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::ReferrerPolicy);
753 if (!referrerPolicy.isNull())
754 m_frame.document()->processReferrerPolicy(referrerPolicy, ReferrerPolicySource::HTTPHeader);
755
756 String headerContentLanguage = m_documentLoader->response().httpHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::ContentLanguage);
757 if (!headerContentLanguage.isEmpty()) {
758 size_t commaIndex = headerContentLanguage.find(',');
759 headerContentLanguage.truncate(commaIndex); // notFound == -1 == don't truncate
760 headerContentLanguage = stripLeadingAndTrailingHTMLSpaces(headerContentLanguage);
761 if (!headerContentLanguage.isEmpty())
762 m_frame.document()->setContentLanguage(headerContentLanguage);
763 }
764 }
765
766 history().restoreDocumentState();
767}
768
769void FrameLoader::finishedParsing()
770{
771 LOG(Loading, "WebCoreLoading %s: Finished parsing", m_frame.tree().uniqueName().string().utf8().data());
772
773 m_frame.injectUserScripts(UserScriptInjectionTime::DocumentEnd);
774
775 if (m_stateMachine.creatingInitialEmptyDocument())
776 return;
777
778 // This can be called from the Frame's destructor, in which case we shouldn't protect ourselves
779 // because doing so will cause us to re-enter the destructor when protector goes out of scope.
780 // Null-checking the FrameView indicates whether or not we're in the destructor.
781 RefPtr<Frame> protector = m_frame.view() ? &m_frame : 0;
782
783 m_client->dispatchDidFinishDocumentLoad();
784
785 scrollToFragmentWithParentBoundary(m_frame.document()->url());
786
787 checkCompleted();
788
789 if (!m_frame.view())
790 return; // We are being destroyed by something checkCompleted called.
791
792 // Check if the scrollbars are really needed for the content.
793 // If not, remove them, relayout, and repaint.
794 m_frame.view()->restoreScrollbar();
795}
796
797void FrameLoader::loadDone(LoadCompletionType type)
798{
799 if (type == LoadCompletionType::Finish)
800 checkCompleted();
801 else
802 scheduleCheckCompleted();
803}
804
805void FrameLoader::subresourceLoadDone(LoadCompletionType type)
806{
807 if (type == LoadCompletionType::Finish)
808 checkLoadComplete();
809 else
810 scheduleCheckLoadComplete();
811}

813bool FrameLoader::preventsParentFromBeingComplete(const Frame& frame) const
814{

818bool FrameLoader::allChildrenAreComplete() const
819{
820 for (Frame* child = m_frame.tree().firstChild(); child; child = child->tree().nextSibling()) {
821 if (preventsParentFromBeingComplete(*child))
822 return false;
823 }
824 return true;

827bool FrameLoader::allAncestorsAreComplete() const
828{
829 for (Frame* ancestor = &m_frame; ancestor; ancestor = ancestor->tree().parent()) {
830 if (!ancestor->loader().m_isComplete)
831 return false;
832 }
833 return true;

835
836void FrameLoader::checkCompleted()
837{
838 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread::isScriptAllowed());
839 m_shouldCallCheckCompleted = false;
840
841 // Have we completed before?
842 if (m_isComplete)
843 return;
844
845 // FIXME: It would be better if resource loads were kicked off after render tree update (or didn't complete synchronously).
846 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=171729
847 if (m_frame.document()->inRenderTreeUpdate()) {
848 scheduleCheckCompleted();
849 return;
850 }
851
852 // Are we still parsing?
853 if (m_frame.document()->parsing())
854 return;
855
856 // Still waiting for images/scripts?
857 if (m_frame.document()->cachedResourceLoader().requestCount())
858 return;
859
860 // Still waiting for elements that don't go through a FrameLoader?
861 if (m_frame.document()->isDelayingLoadEvent())
862 return;
863
864 auto* scriptableParser = m_frame.document()->scriptableDocumentParser();
865 if (scriptableParser && scriptableParser->hasScriptsWaitingForStylesheets())
866 return;
867
868 // Any frame that hasn't completed yet?
869 if (!allChildrenAreComplete())
870 return;
871
872 // Important not to protect earlier in this function, because earlier parts
873 // of this function can be called in the frame's destructor, and it's not legal
874 // to ref an object while it's being destroyed.
875 Ref<Frame> protect(m_frame);
876
877 // OK, completed.
878 m_isComplete = true;
879 m_requestedHistoryItem = nullptr;
880 m_frame.document()->setReadyState(Document::Complete);
881
882 checkCallImplicitClose(); // if we didn't do it before
883
884 m_frame.navigationScheduler().startTimer();
885
886 completed();
887 if (m_frame.page())
888 checkLoadComplete();
889}
890
891void FrameLoader::checkTimerFired()
892{
893 checkCompletenessNow();
894}
895
896void FrameLoader::checkCompletenessNow()
897{
898 Ref<Frame> protect(m_frame);
899
900 if (Page* page = m_frame.page()) {
901 if (page->defersLoading())
902 return;
903 }
904 if (m_shouldCallCheckCompleted)
905 checkCompleted();
906 if (m_shouldCallCheckLoadComplete)
907 checkLoadComplete();
908}
909
910void FrameLoader::startCheckCompleteTimer()
911{
912 if (!(m_shouldCallCheckCompleted || m_shouldCallCheckLoadComplete))
913 return;
914 if (m_checkTimer.isActive())
915 return;
916 m_checkTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
917}
918
919void FrameLoader::scheduleCheckCompleted()
920{
921 m_shouldCallCheckCompleted = true;
922 startCheckCompleteTimer();
923}
924
925void FrameLoader::scheduleCheckLoadComplete()
926{
927 m_shouldCallCheckLoadComplete = true;
928 startCheckCompleteTimer();
929}
930
931void FrameLoader::checkCallImplicitClose()
932{
933 if (m_didCallImplicitClose || m_frame.document()->parsing() || m_frame.document()->isDelayingLoadEvent())
934 return;
935
936 if (!allChildrenAreComplete())
937 return; // still got a frame running -> too early
938
939 m_didCallImplicitClose = true;
940 m_wasUnloadEventEmitted = false;
941 m_frame.document()->implicitClose();
942}
943
944void FrameLoader::loadURLIntoChildFrame(const URL& url, const String& referer, Frame* childFrame)
945{
946 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "loadURLIntoChildFrame: frame load started");
947
948 ASSERT(childFrame);
949
950#if ENABLE(WEB_ARCHIVE) || ENABLE(MHTML)
951 if (auto activeLoader = activeDocumentLoader()) {
952 if (auto subframeArchive = activeLoader->popArchiveForSubframe(childFrame->tree().uniqueName(), url)) {
953 childFrame->loader().loadArchive(RefPtr<Archive> { subframeArchive }.releaseNonNull());
954 return;
955 }
956 }
957#endif
958
959 // If we're moving in the back/forward list, we might want to replace the content
960 // of this child frame with whatever was there at that point.
961 auto* parentItem = history().currentItem();
962 if (parentItem && parentItem->children().size() && isBackForwardLoadType(loadType()) && !m_frame.document()->loadEventFinished()) {
963 if (auto* childItem = parentItem->childItemWithTarget(childFrame->tree().uniqueName())) {
964 childFrame->loader().m_requestedHistoryItem = childItem;
965 childFrame->loader().loadDifferentDocumentItem(*childItem, nullptr, loadType(), MayAttemptCacheOnlyLoadForFormSubmissionItem, ShouldTreatAsContinuingLoad::No);
966 return;
967 }
968 }
969
970 auto* lexicalFrame = lexicalFrameFromCommonVM();
971 auto initiatedByMainFrame = lexicalFrame && lexicalFrame->isMainFrame() ? InitiatedByMainFrame::Yes : InitiatedByMainFrame::Unknown;
972
973 FrameLoadRequest frameLoadRequest { *m_frame.document(), m_frame.document()->securityOrigin(), { url }, "_self"_s, initiatedByMainFrame };
974 frameLoadRequest.setNewFrameOpenerPolicy(NewFrameOpenerPolicy::Suppress);
975 frameLoadRequest.setLockBackForwardList(LockBackForwardList::Yes);
976 childFrame->loader().loadURL(WTFMove(frameLoadRequest), referer, FrameLoadType::RedirectWithLockedBackForwardList, nullptr, { }, std::nullopt, [] { });
977}
978
979#if ENABLE(WEB_ARCHIVE) || ENABLE(MHTML)
980
981void FrameLoader::loadArchive(Ref<Archive>&& archive)
982{
983 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "loadArchive: frame load started");
984
985 ArchiveResource* mainResource = archive->mainResource();
986 ASSERT(mainResource);
987 if (!mainResource)
988 return;
989
990 ResourceResponse response(URL(), mainResource->mimeType(), mainResource->data().size(), mainResource->textEncoding());
991 SubstituteData substituteData(&mainResource->data(), URL(), response, SubstituteData::SessionHistoryVisibility::Hidden);
992
993 ResourceRequest request(mainResource->url());
994
995 auto documentLoader = m_client->createDocumentLoader(request, substituteData);
996 documentLoader->setArchive(WTFMove(archive));
997 load(documentLoader.get());
998}

1000#endif // ENABLE(WEB_ARCHIVE) || ENABLE(MHTML)

1002String FrameLoader::outgoingReferrer() const
1003{
1004 // See http://www.whatwg.org/specs/web-apps/current-work/#fetching-resources
1005 // for why we walk the parent chain for srcdoc documents.
1006 Frame* frame = &m_frame;
1007 while (frame && frame->document()->isSrcdocDocument()) {
1008 frame = frame->tree().parent();
1009 // Srcdoc documents cannot be top-level documents, by definition,
1010 // because they need to be contained in iframes with the srcdoc.
1011 ASSERT(frame);
1012 }
1013 if (!frame)
1014 return emptyString();
1015 return frame->loader().m_outgoingReferrer;
1016}

1026 return true;

1032void FrameLoader::setOpener(Frame* opener)
1033{
1034 if (m_opener && !opener)
1035 m_client->didDisownOpener();
1036
1037 if (m_opener) {
1038 // When setOpener is called in ~FrameLoader, opener's m_frameLoader is already cleared.
1039 auto& openerFrameLoader = m_opener == &m_frame ? *this : m_opener->loader();
1040 openerFrameLoader.m_openedFrames.remove(m_frame);
1041 }
1042 if (opener) {
1043 opener->loader().m_openedFrames.add(&m_frame);
1044 if (auto* page = m_frame.page())
1045 page->setOpenedByDOMWithOpener();
1046 }
1047 m_opener = makeWeakPtr(opener);
1048
1049 if (m_frame.document())
1050 m_frame.document()->initSecurityContext();
1051}

1093// This does the same kind of work that didOpenURL does, except it relies on the fact
1094// that a higher level already checked that the URLs match and the scrolling is the right thing to do.
1095void FrameLoader::loadInSameDocument(const URL& url, SerializedScriptValue* stateObject, bool isNewNavigation)
1096{
1097 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "loadInSameDocument: frame load started");
1098
1099 // If we have a state object, we cannot also be a new navigation.
1100 ASSERT(!stateObject || (stateObject && !isNewNavigation));
1101
1102 // Update the data source's request with the new URL to fake the URL change
1103 URL oldURL = m_frame.document()->url();
1104 m_frame.document()->setURL(url);
1105 setOutgoingReferrer(url);
1106 documentLoader()->replaceRequestURLForSameDocumentNavigation(url);
1107 if (isNewNavigation && !shouldTreatURLAsSameAsCurrent(url) && !stateObject) {
1108 // NB: must happen after replaceRequestURLForSameDocumentNavigation(), since we add
1109 // based on the current request. Must also happen before we openURL and displace the
1110 // scroll position, since adding the BF item will save away scroll state.
1111
1112 // NB2: If we were loading a long, slow doc, and the user fragment navigated before
1113 // it was done, currItem is now set the that slow doc, and prevItem is whatever was
1114 // before it. Adding the b/f item will bump the slow doc down to prevItem, even
1115 // though its load is not yet done. I think this all works out OK, for one because
1116 // we have already saved away the scroll and doc state for the long slow load,
1117 // but it's not an obvious case.
1118
1119 history().updateBackForwardListForFragmentScroll();
1120 }
1121
1122 bool hashChange = equalIgnoringFragmentIdentifier(url, oldURL) && !equalRespectingNullity(url.fragmentIdentifier(), oldURL.fragmentIdentifier());
1123
1124 history().updateForSameDocumentNavigation();
1125
1126 // If we were in the autoscroll/panScroll mode we want to stop it before following the link to the anchor
1127 if (hashChange)
1128 m_frame.eventHandler().stopAutoscrollTimer();
1129
1130 // It's important to model this as a load that starts and immediately finishes.
1131 // Otherwise, the parent frame may think we never finished loading.
1132 started();
1133
1134 if (auto* ownerElement = m_frame.ownerElement()) {
1135 auto* ownerRenderer = ownerElement->renderer();
1136 auto* view = m_frame.view();
1137 if (is<RenderWidget>(ownerRenderer) && view)
1138 downcast<RenderWidget>(*ownerRenderer).setWidget(view);
1139 }
1140
1141 // We need to scroll to the fragment whether or not a hash change occurred, since
1142 // the user might have scrolled since the previous navigation.
1143 scrollToFragmentWithParentBoundary(url, isNewNavigation);
1144
1145 m_isComplete = false;
1146 checkCompleted();
1147
1148 if (isNewNavigation) {
1149 // This will clear previousItem from the rest of the frame tree that didn't
1150 // doing any loading. We need to make a pass on this now, since for fragment
1151 // navigation we'll not go through a real load and reach Completed state.
1152 checkLoadComplete();
1153 }
1154
1155 m_client->dispatchDidNavigateWithinPage();
1156
1157 m_frame.document()->statePopped(stateObject ? Ref<SerializedScriptValue> { *stateObject } : SerializedScriptValue::nullValue());
1158 m_client->dispatchDidPopStateWithinPage();
1159
1160 if (hashChange) {
1161 m_frame.document()->enqueueHashchangeEvent(oldURL.string(), url.string());
1162 m_client->dispatchDidChangeLocationWithinPage();
1163 }
1164
1165 // FrameLoaderClient::didFinishLoad() tells the internal load delegate the load finished with no error
1166 m_client->didFinishLoad();
1167}

1169bool FrameLoader::isComplete() const
1170{
1171 return m_isComplete;
1172}
1173
1174void FrameLoader::completed()
1175{
1176 Ref<Frame> protect(m_frame);
1177
1178 for (Frame* descendant = m_frame.tree().traverseNext(&m_frame); descendant; descendant = descendant->tree().traverseNext(&m_frame))
1179 descendant->navigationScheduler().startTimer();
1180
1181 if (Frame* parent = m_frame.tree().parent())
1182 parent->loader().checkCompleted();
1183
1184 if (m_frame.view())
1185 m_frame.view()->maintainScrollPositionAtAnchor(nullptr);
1186}

1191 frame->loader().m_isComplete = false;
1192}

1200

1218
1219void FrameLoader::loadFrameRequest(FrameLoadRequest&& request, Event* event, RefPtr<FormState>&& formState, std::optional<PrivateClickMeasurement>&& privateClickMeasurement)
1220{
1221 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "loadFrameRequest: frame load started");
1222
1223 // Protect frame from getting blown away inside dispatchBeforeLoadEvent in loadWithDocumentLoader.
1224 auto protectFrame = makeRef(m_frame);
1225
1226 URL url = request.resourceRequest().url();
1227
1228 ASSERT(m_frame.document());
1229 if (!request.requesterSecurityOrigin().canDisplay(url)) {
1230 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "loadFrameRequest: canceling - Not allowed to load local resource");
1231 reportLocalLoadFailed(&m_frame, url.stringCenterEllipsizedToLength());
1232 return;
1233 }
1234
1235 if (!portAllowed(url)) {
1236 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "loadFrameRequest: canceling - port not allowed");
1237 reportBlockedLoadFailed(m_frame, url);
1238 return;
1239 }
1240
1241 String argsReferrer = request.resourceRequest().httpReferrer();
1242 if (argsReferrer.isEmpty())
1243 argsReferrer = outgoingReferrer();
1244
1245 ReferrerPolicy referrerPolicy = request.referrerPolicy();
1246 if (referrerPolicy == ReferrerPolicy::EmptyString)
1247 referrerPolicy = m_frame.document()->referrerPolicy();
1248 String referrer = SecurityPolicy::generateReferrerHeader(referrerPolicy, url, argsReferrer);
1249
1250 FrameLoadType loadType;
1251 if (request.resourceRequest().cachePolicy() == ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData)
1252 loadType = FrameLoadType::Reload;
1253 else if (request.lockBackForwardList() == LockBackForwardList::Yes)
1254 loadType = FrameLoadType::RedirectWithLockedBackForwardList;
1255 else
1256 loadType = FrameLoadType::Standard;
1257
1258 auto completionHandler = [this, protectedFrame = makeRef(m_frame), formState = makeWeakPtr(formState.get()), frameName = request.frameName()] {
1259 // FIXME: It's possible this targetFrame will not be the same frame that was targeted by the actual
1260 // load if frame names have changed.
1261 Frame* sourceFrame = formState ? formState->sourceDocument().frame() : &m_frame;
1262 if (!sourceFrame)
1263 sourceFrame = &m_frame;
1264 Frame* targetFrame = sourceFrame->loader().findFrameForNavigation(frameName);
1265 if (targetFrame && targetFrame != sourceFrame) {
1266 if (Page* page = targetFrame->page())
1267 page->chrome().focus();
1268 }
1269 };
1270
1271 if (request.resourceRequest().httpMethod() == "POST")
1272 loadPostRequest(WTFMove(request), referrer, loadType, event, WTFMove(formState), WTFMove(completionHandler));
1273 else
1274 loadURL(WTFMove(request), referrer, loadType, event, WTFMove(formState), WTFMove(privateClickMeasurement), WTFMove(completionHandler));
1275}
1276
1277static ShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToApply(Frame& currentFrame, InitiatedByMainFrame initiatedByMainFrame, ShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy propagatedPolicy)
1278{
1279 if (UserGestureIndicator::processingUserGesture())
1280 return ShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy::ShouldAllow;
1281
1282 if (initiatedByMainFrame == InitiatedByMainFrame::Yes)
1283 return propagatedPolicy;
1284
1285 if (!currentFrame.isMainFrame())
1286 return ShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy::ShouldNotAllow;
1287
1288 return propagatedPolicy;
1289}
1290
1291static ShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToApply(Frame& currentFrame, const FrameLoadRequest& frameLoadRequest)
1292{
1293 return shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToApply(currentFrame, frameLoadRequest.initiatedByMainFrame(), frameLoadRequest.shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy());
1294}

1296static void applyShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToNewDocumentLoader(Frame& frame, DocumentLoader& documentLoader, InitiatedByMainFrame initiatedByMainFrame, ShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy propagatedPolicy)
1297{
1298 documentLoader.setShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy(shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToApply(frame, initiatedByMainFrame, propagatedPolicy));
1299}
1300
1301static void applyShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToNewDocumentLoader(Frame& frame, DocumentLoader& documentLoader, const FrameLoadRequest& frameLoadRequest)
1302{
1303 documentLoader.setShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy(shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToApply(frame, frameLoadRequest));
1304}

1315
1316void FrameLoader::loadURL(FrameLoadRequest&& frameLoadRequest, const String& referrer, FrameLoadType newLoadType, Event* event, RefPtr<FormState>&& formState, std::optional<PrivateClickMeasurement>&& privateClickMeasurement, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
1317{
1318 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "loadURL: frame load started");
1319 ASSERT(frameLoadRequest.resourceRequest().httpMethod() == "GET");
1320
1321 CompletionHandlerCallingScope completionHandlerCaller(WTFMove(completionHandler));
1322 if (m_inStopAllLoaders || m_inClearProvisionalLoadForPolicyCheck)
1323 return;
1324
1325 Ref<Frame> protect(m_frame);
1326
1327 // Anchor target is ignored when the download attribute is set since it will download the hyperlink rather than follow it.
1328 String effectiveFrameName = frameLoadRequest.downloadAttribute().isNull() ? frameLoadRequest.frameName() : String();
1329 bool isFormSubmission = formState;
1330
1331 // The search for a target frame is done earlier in the case of form submission.
1332 auto targetFrame = isFormSubmission ? nullptr : makeRefPtr(findFrameForNavigation(effectiveFrameName));
1333 if (targetFrame && targetFrame != &m_frame) {
1334 frameLoadRequest.setFrameName("_self");
1335 targetFrame->loader().loadURL(WTFMove(frameLoadRequest), referrer, newLoadType, event, WTFMove(formState), WTFMove(privateClickMeasurement), completionHandlerCaller.release());
1336 return;
1337 }
1338
1339 const URL& newURL = frameLoadRequest.resourceRequest().url();
1340 ResourceRequest request(newURL);
1341 if (!referrer.isEmpty())
1342 request.setHTTPReferrer(referrer);
1343
1344 updateRequestAndAddExtraFields(request, IsMainResource::Yes, newLoadType);
1345
1346 ASSERT(newLoadType != FrameLoadType::Same);
1347
1348 if (!isNavigationAllowed())
1349 return;
1350
1351 NavigationAction action { frameLoadRequest.requester(), request, frameLoadRequest.initiatedByMainFrame(), newLoadType, isFormSubmission, event, frameLoadRequest.shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy(), frameLoadRequest.downloadAttribute() };
1352 action.setLockHistory(frameLoadRequest.lockHistory());
1353 action.setLockBackForwardList(frameLoadRequest.lockBackForwardList());
1354 if (privateClickMeasurement && m_frame.isMainFrame())
1355 action.setPrivateClickMeasurement(WTFMove(*privateClickMeasurement));
1356
1357 NewFrameOpenerPolicy openerPolicy = frameLoadRequest.newFrameOpenerPolicy();
1358 AllowNavigationToInvalidURL allowNavigationToInvalidURL = frameLoadRequest.allowNavigationToInvalidURL();
1359 if (!targetFrame && !effectiveFrameName.isEmpty()) {
1360 action = action.copyWithShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy(shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToApply(m_frame, frameLoadRequest));
1361 policyChecker().checkNewWindowPolicy(WTFMove(action), WTFMove(request), WTFMove(formState), effectiveFrameName, [this, allowNavigationToInvalidURL, openerPolicy, completionHandler = completionHandlerCaller.release()] (const ResourceRequest& request, WeakPtr<FormState>&& formState, const String& frameName, const NavigationAction& action, ShouldContinuePolicyCheck shouldContinue) mutable {
1362 continueLoadAfterNewWindowPolicy(request, formState.get(), frameName, action, shouldContinue, allowNavigationToInvalidURL, openerPolicy);
1363 completionHandler();
1364 });
1365 return;
1366 }
1367
1368 RefPtr<DocumentLoader> oldDocumentLoader = m_documentLoader;
1369
1370 bool sameURL = shouldTreatURLAsSameAsCurrent(newURL);
1371 const String& httpMethod = request.httpMethod();
1372
1373 // Make sure to do scroll to fragment processing even if the URL is
1374 // exactly the same so pages with '#' links and DHTML side effects
1375 // work properly.
1376 if (shouldPerformFragmentNavigation(isFormSubmission, httpMethod, newLoadType, newURL)) {
1377 oldDocumentLoader->setTriggeringAction(WTFMove(action));
1378 oldDocumentLoader->setLastCheckedRequest(ResourceRequest());
1379 policyChecker().stopCheck();
1380 policyChecker().setLoadType(newLoadType);
1381 RELEASE_ASSERT(!isBackForwardLoadType(newLoadType) || history().provisionalItem());
1382 policyChecker().checkNavigationPolicy(WTFMove(request), ResourceResponse { } /* redirectResponse */, oldDocumentLoader.get(), WTFMove(formState), [this, protectedFrame = makeRef(m_frame)] (const ResourceRequest& request, WeakPtr<FormState>&&, NavigationPolicyDecision navigationPolicyDecision) {
1383 continueFragmentScrollAfterNavigationPolicy(request, navigationPolicyDecision == NavigationPolicyDecision::ContinueLoad);
1384 }, PolicyDecisionMode::Synchronous);
1385 return;
1386 }
1387
1388 // Must grab this now, since this load may stop the previous load and clear this flag.
1389 bool isRedirect = m_quickRedirectComing;
1390#if USE(SYSTEM_PREVIEW)
1391 bool isSystemPreview = frameLoadRequest.isSystemPreview();
1392 if (isSystemPreview)
1393 request.setSystemPreviewInfo(frameLoadRequest.systemPreviewInfo());
1394#endif
1395 loadWithNavigationAction(request, WTFMove(action), newLoadType, WTFMove(formState), allowNavigationToInvalidURL, [this, isRedirect, sameURL, newLoadType, protectedFrame = makeRef(m_frame), completionHandler = completionHandlerCaller.release()] () mutable {
1396 if (isRedirect) {
1397 m_quickRedirectComing = false;
1398 if (m_provisionalDocumentLoader)
1399 m_provisionalDocumentLoader->setIsClientRedirect(true);
1400 else if (m_policyDocumentLoader)
1401 m_policyDocumentLoader->setIsClientRedirect(true);
1402 } else if (sameURL && !isReload(newLoadType)) {
1403 // Example of this case are sites that reload the same URL with a different cookie
1404 // driving the generated content, or a master frame with links that drive a target
1405 // frame, where the user has clicked on the same link repeatedly.
1406 m_loadType = FrameLoadType::Same;
1407 }
1408 completionHandler();
1409 });
1410}
1411
1412SubstituteData FrameLoader::defaultSubstituteDataForURL(const URL& url)
1413{
1414 if (!shouldTreatURLAsSrcdocDocument(url))
1415 return SubstituteData();
1416 auto& srcdoc = m_frame.ownerElement()->attributeWithoutSynchronization(srcdocAttr);
1417 ASSERT(!srcdoc.isNull());
1418 CString encodedSrcdoc = srcdoc.string().utf8();
1419
1420 ResourceResponse response(URL(), "text/html"_s, encodedSrcdoc.length(), "UTF-8"_s);
1421 return SubstituteData(SharedBuffer::create(encodedSrcdoc.data(), encodedSrcdoc.length()), URL(), response, SubstituteData::SessionHistoryVisibility::Hidden);
1422}
1423
1424void FrameLoader::load(FrameLoadRequest&& request)
1425{
1426 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "load (FrameLoadRequest): frame load started");
1427
1428 if (m_inStopAllLoaders || m_inClearProvisionalLoadForPolicyCheck)
1429 return;
1430
1431 if (!request.frameName().isEmpty()) {
1432 Frame* frame = findFrameForNavigation(request.frameName());
1433 if (frame) {
1434 request.setShouldCheckNewWindowPolicy(false);
1435 if (&frame->loader() != this) {
1436 frame->loader().load(WTFMove(request));
1437 return;
1438 }
1439 }
1440 }
1441
1442 if (request.shouldCheckNewWindowPolicy()) {
1443 NavigationAction action { request.requester(), request.resourceRequest(), InitiatedByMainFrame::Unknown, NavigationType::Other, request.shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy() };
1444 policyChecker().checkNewWindowPolicy(WTFMove(action), WTFMove(request.resourceRequest()), { }, request.frameName(), [this] (const ResourceRequest& request, WeakPtr<FormState>&& formState, const String& frameName, const NavigationAction& action, ShouldContinuePolicyCheck shouldContinue) {
1445 continueLoadAfterNewWindowPolicy(request, formState.get(), frameName, action, shouldContinue, AllowNavigationToInvalidURL::Yes, NewFrameOpenerPolicy::Suppress);
1446 });
1447
1448 return;
1449 }
1450
1451 if (!request.hasSubstituteData())
1452 request.setSubstituteData(defaultSubstituteDataForURL(request.resourceRequest().url()));
1453
1454 Ref<DocumentLoader> loader = m_client->createDocumentLoader(request.resourceRequest(), request.substituteData());
1455 loader->setAllowsWebArchiveForMainFrame(request.isRequestFromClientOrUserInput());
1456 loader->setAllowsDataURLsForMainFrame(request.isRequestFromClientOrUserInput());
1457 addSameSiteInfoToRequestIfNeeded(loader->request());
1458 applyShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToNewDocumentLoader(m_frame, loader, request);
1459
1460 if (request.shouldTreatAsContinuingLoad()) {
1461 loader->setClientRedirectSourceForHistory(request.clientRedirectSourceForHistory());
1462 if (request.lockBackForwardList() == LockBackForwardList::Yes) {
1463 loader->setIsClientRedirect(true);
1464 m_loadType = FrameLoadType::RedirectWithLockedBackForwardList;
1465 }
1466 }
1467
1468 SetForScope<LoadContinuingState> continuingLoadGuard(m_currentLoadContinuingState, request.shouldTreatAsContinuingLoad() ? LoadContinuingState::ContinuingWithRequest : LoadContinuingState::NotContinuing);
1469 load(loader.get());
1470}
1471
1472void FrameLoader::loadWithNavigationAction(const ResourceRequest& request, NavigationAction&& action, FrameLoadType type, RefPtr<FormState>&& formState, AllowNavigationToInvalidURL allowNavigationToInvalidURL, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
1473{
1474 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "loadWithNavigationAction: frame load started");
1475
1476 Ref<DocumentLoader> loader = m_client->createDocumentLoader(request, defaultSubstituteDataForURL(request.url()));
1477 applyShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToNewDocumentLoader(m_frame, loader, action.initiatedByMainFrame(), action.shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy());
1478
1479 if (action.lockHistory() == LockHistory::Yes && m_documentLoader)
1480 loader->setClientRedirectSourceForHistory(m_documentLoader->didCreateGlobalHistoryEntry() ? m_documentLoader->urlForHistory().string() : m_documentLoader->clientRedirectSourceForHistory());
1481
1482 loader->setTriggeringAction(WTFMove(action));
1483 if (m_documentLoader)
1484 loader->setOverrideEncoding(m_documentLoader->overrideEncoding());
1485
1486 loadWithDocumentLoader(loader.ptr(), type, WTFMove(formState), allowNavigationToInvalidURL, WTFMove(completionHandler));
1487}
1488
1489void FrameLoader::load(DocumentLoader& newDocumentLoader)
1490{
1491 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "load (DocumentLoader): frame load started");
1492
1493 ResourceRequest& r = newDocumentLoader.request();
1494 // FIXME: Using m_loadType seems wrong here.
1495 // If we are only preparing to load the main resource, that is previous load's load type!
1496 updateRequestAndAddExtraFields(r, IsMainResource::Yes, m_loadType, ShouldUpdateAppBoundValue::No);
1497 FrameLoadType type;
1498
1499 if (shouldTreatURLAsSameAsCurrent(newDocumentLoader.originalRequest().url())) {
1500 r.setCachePolicy(ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData);
1501 type = FrameLoadType::Same;
1502 } else if (shouldTreatURLAsSameAsCurrent(newDocumentLoader.unreachableURL()) && isReload(m_loadType))
1503 type = m_loadType;
1504 else if (m_loadType == FrameLoadType::RedirectWithLockedBackForwardList && ((!newDocumentLoader.unreachableURL().isEmpty() && newDocumentLoader.substituteData().isValid()) || shouldTreatCurrentLoadAsContinuingLoad()))
1505 type = FrameLoadType::RedirectWithLockedBackForwardList;
1506 else
1507 type = FrameLoadType::Standard;
1508
1509 if (m_documentLoader)
1510 newDocumentLoader.setOverrideEncoding(m_documentLoader->overrideEncoding());
1511
1512 // When we loading alternate content for an unreachable URL that we're
1513 // visiting in the history list, we treat it as a reload so the history list
1514 // is appropriately maintained.
1515 //
1516 // FIXME: This seems like a dangerous overloading of the meaning of "FrameLoadType::Reload" ...
1517 // shouldn't a more explicit type of reload be defined, that means roughly
1518 // "load without affecting history" ?
1519 if (shouldReloadToHandleUnreachableURL(newDocumentLoader)) {
1520 // shouldReloadToHandleUnreachableURL returns true only when the original load type is back-forward.
1521 // In this case we should save the document state now. Otherwise the state can be lost because load type is
1522 // changed and updateForBackForwardNavigation() will not be called when loading is committed.
1523 history().saveDocumentAndScrollState();
1524
1525 ASSERT(type == FrameLoadType::Standard);
1526 type = FrameLoadType::Reload;
1527 }
1528
1529 loadWithDocumentLoader(&newDocumentLoader, type, nullptr, AllowNavigationToInvalidURL::Yes);
1530}
1531
1532void FrameLoader::loadWithDocumentLoader(DocumentLoader* loader, FrameLoadType type, RefPtr<FormState>&& formState, AllowNavigationToInvalidURL allowNavigationToInvalidURL, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
1533{
1534 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "loadWithDocumentLoader: frame load started");
1535
1536 // Retain because dispatchBeforeLoadEvent may release the last reference to it.
1537 Ref<Frame> protect(m_frame);
1538
1539 CompletionHandlerCallingScope completionHandlerCaller(WTFMove(completionHandler));
1540
1541 ASSERT(m_client->hasWebView());
1542
1543 // Unfortunately the view must be non-nil, this is ultimately due
1544 // to parser requiring a FrameView. We should fix this dependency.
1545
1546 ASSERT(m_frame.view());
1547
1548 if (!isNavigationAllowed())
1549 return;
1550
1551 if (m_frame.document())
1552 m_previousURL = m_frame.document()->url();
1553
1554 const URL& newURL = loader->request().url();
1555
1556 // Only the first iframe navigation or the first iframe navigation after about:blank should be reported.
1557 // https://www.w3.org/TR/resource-timing-2/#resources-included-in-the-performanceresourcetiming-interface
1558 if (m_shouldReportResourceTimingToParentFrame && !m_previousURL.isNull() && m_previousURL != aboutBlankURL())
1559 m_shouldReportResourceTimingToParentFrame = false;
1560
1561 // Log main frame navigation types.
1562 if (m_frame.isMainFrame()) {
1563 if (auto* page = m_frame.page()) {
1564 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "loadWithDocumentLoader: main frame load started");
1565 page->mainFrameLoadStarted(newURL, type);
1566 page->performanceLogging().didReachPointOfInterest(PerformanceLogging::MainFrameLoadStarted);
1567 }
1568 }
1569
1570 policyChecker().setLoadType(type);
1571 RELEASE_ASSERT(!isBackForwardLoadType(type) || history().provisionalItem());
1572 bool isFormSubmission = formState;
1573
1574 const String& httpMethod = loader->request().httpMethod();
1575
1576 if (shouldPerformFragmentNavigation(isFormSubmission, httpMethod, policyChecker().loadType(), newURL)) {
1577 RefPtr<DocumentLoader> oldDocumentLoader = m_documentLoader;
1578 NavigationAction action { *m_frame.document(), loader->request(), InitiatedByMainFrame::Unknown, policyChecker().loadType(), isFormSubmission };
1579
1580 oldDocumentLoader->setTriggeringAction(WTFMove(action));
1581 oldDocumentLoader->setLastCheckedRequest(ResourceRequest());
1582 policyChecker().stopCheck();
1583 RELEASE_ASSERT(!isBackForwardLoadType(policyChecker().loadType()) || history().provisionalItem());
1584 policyChecker().checkNavigationPolicy(ResourceRequest(loader->request()), ResourceResponse { } /* redirectResponse */, oldDocumentLoader.get(), WTFMove(formState), [this, protectedFrame = makeRef(m_frame)] (const ResourceRequest& request, WeakPtr<FormState>&&, NavigationPolicyDecision navigationPolicyDecision) {
1585 continueFragmentScrollAfterNavigationPolicy(request, navigationPolicyDecision == NavigationPolicyDecision::ContinueLoad);
1586 }, PolicyDecisionMode::Synchronous);
1587 return;
1588 }
1589
1590 if (Frame* parent = m_frame.tree().parent())
1591 loader->setOverrideEncoding(parent->loader().documentLoader()->overrideEncoding());
1592
1593 policyChecker().stopCheck();
1594 setPolicyDocumentLoader(loader);
1595 if (loader->triggeringAction().isEmpty())
1596 loader->setTriggeringAction({ *m_frame.document(), loader->request(), InitiatedByMainFrame::Unknown, policyChecker().loadType(), isFormSubmission });
1597
1598 if (Element* ownerElement = m_frame.ownerElement()) {
1599 // We skip dispatching the beforeload event if we've already
1600 // committed a real document load because the event would leak
1601 // subsequent activity by the frame which the parent frame isn't
1602 // supposed to learn. For example, if the child frame navigated to
1603 // a new URL, the parent frame shouldn't learn the URL.
1604 if (!m_stateMachine.committedFirstRealDocumentLoad()
1605 && !ownerElement->dispatchBeforeLoadEvent(loader->request().url().string())) {
1606 continueLoadAfterNavigationPolicy(loader->request(), formState.get(), NavigationPolicyDecision::IgnoreLoad, allowNavigationToInvalidURL);
1607 return;
1608 }
1609 }
1610
1611 m_frame.navigationScheduler().cancel(NewLoadInProgress::Yes);
1612
1613 if (shouldTreatCurrentLoadAsContinuingLoad()) {
1614 continueLoadAfterNavigationPolicy(loader->request(), formState.get(), NavigationPolicyDecision::ContinueLoad, allowNavigationToInvalidURL);
1615 return;
1616 }
1617
1618 RELEASE_ASSERT(!isBackForwardLoadType(policyChecker().loadType()) || history().provisionalItem());
1619 policyChecker().checkNavigationPolicy(ResourceRequest(loader->request()), ResourceResponse { } /* redirectResponse */, loader, WTFMove(formState), [this, protectedFrame = makeRef(m_frame), allowNavigationToInvalidURL, completionHandler = completionHandlerCaller.release()] (const ResourceRequest& request, WeakPtr<FormState>&& formState, NavigationPolicyDecision navigationPolicyDecision) mutable {
1620 continueLoadAfterNavigationPolicy(request, formState.get(), navigationPolicyDecision, allowNavigationToInvalidURL);
1621 completionHandler();
1622 }, PolicyDecisionMode::Asynchronous);
1623}

1630 SetForScope<bool> change(m_inClearProvisionalLoadForPolicyCheck, true);
1631 m_provisionalDocumentLoader->stopLoading();
1632 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "clearProvisionalLoadForPolicyCheck: Clearing provisional document loader (m_provisionalDocumentLoader=%p)", m_provisionalDocumentLoader.get());
1633 setProvisionalDocumentLoader(nullptr);

1657bool FrameLoader::willLoadMediaElementURL(URL& url, Node& initiatorNode)
1658{
1659#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1660 // MobileStore depends on the iOS 4.0 era client delegate method because webView:resource:willSendRequest:redirectResponse:fromDataSource
1661 // doesn't let them tell when a load request is coming from a media element. See <rdar://problem/8266916> for more details.
1662 if (IOSApplication::isMobileStore())
1663 return m_client->shouldLoadMediaElementURL(url);
1664#endif
1665
1666 ResourceRequest request(url);
1667 request.setInspectorInitiatorNodeIdentifier(InspectorInstrumentation::identifierForNode(initiatorNode));
1668
1669 unsigned long identifier;
1670 ResourceError error;
1671 requestFromDelegate(request, identifier, error);
1672 notifier().sendRemainingDelegateMessages(m_documentLoader.get(), identifier, request, ResourceResponse(url, String(), -1, String()), 0, -1, -1, error);
1673
1674 url = request.url();
1675
1676 return error.isNull();
1677}
1678
1679bool FrameLoader::shouldReloadToHandleUnreachableURL(DocumentLoader& docLoader)
1680{
1681 URL unreachableURL = docLoader.unreachableURL();
1682
1683 if (unreachableURL.isEmpty())
1684 return false;
1685
1686 if (!isBackForwardLoadType(policyChecker().loadType()))
1687 return false;
1688
1689 // We only treat unreachableURLs specially during the delegate callbacks
1690 // for provisional load errors and navigation policy decisions. The former
1691 // case handles well-formed URLs that can't be loaded, and the latter
1692 // case handles malformed URLs and unknown schemes. Loading alternate content
1693 // at other times behaves like a standard load.
1694 if (policyChecker().delegateIsDecidingNavigationPolicy() || policyChecker().delegateIsHandlingUnimplementablePolicy())
1695 return m_policyDocumentLoader && unreachableURL == m_policyDocumentLoader->request().url();
1696
1697 return unreachableURL == m_provisionalLoadErrorBeingHandledURL;
1698}

1700void FrameLoader::reloadWithOverrideEncoding(const String& encoding)
1701{
1702 if (!m_documentLoader)
1703 return;
1704
1705 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "reloadWithOverrideEncoding: frame load started");
1706
1707 ResourceRequest request = m_documentLoader->request();
1708 URL unreachableURL = m_documentLoader->unreachableURL();
1709 if (!unreachableURL.isEmpty())
1710 request.setURL(unreachableURL);
1711
1712 // FIXME: If the resource is a result of form submission and is not cached, the form will be silently resubmitted.
1713 // We should ask the user for confirmation in this case.
1714 request.setCachePolicy(ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReturnCacheDataElseLoad);
1715
1716 Ref<DocumentLoader> loader = m_client->createDocumentLoader(request, defaultSubstituteDataForURL(request.url()));
1717 applyShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToNewDocumentLoader(m_frame, loader, InitiatedByMainFrame::Unknown, m_documentLoader->shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToPropagate());
1718
1719 setPolicyDocumentLoader(loader.ptr());
1720
1721 loader->setOverrideEncoding(encoding);
1722
1723 loadWithDocumentLoader(loader.ptr(), FrameLoadType::Reload, { }, AllowNavigationToInvalidURL::Yes);
1724}
1725
1726void FrameLoader::reload(OptionSet<ReloadOption> options)
1727{
1728 if (!m_documentLoader)
1729 return;
1730
1731 // If a window is created by javascript, its main frame can have an empty but non-nil URL.
1732 // Reloading in this case will lose the current contents (see 4151001).
1733 if (m_documentLoader->request().url().isEmpty())
1734 return;
1735
1736 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "reload: frame load started");
1737
1738 // Replace error-page URL with the URL we were trying to reach.
1739 ResourceRequest initialRequest = m_documentLoader->request();
1740 URL unreachableURL = m_documentLoader->unreachableURL();
1741 if (!unreachableURL.isEmpty())
1742 initialRequest.setURL(unreachableURL);
1743
1744 // Create a new document loader for the reload, this will become m_documentLoader eventually,
1745 // but first it has to be the "policy" document loader, and then the "provisional" document loader.
1746 Ref<DocumentLoader> loader = m_client->createDocumentLoader(initialRequest, defaultSubstituteDataForURL(initialRequest.url()));
1747 loader->setAllowsWebArchiveForMainFrame(m_documentLoader->allowsWebArchiveForMainFrame());
1748 loader->setAllowsDataURLsForMainFrame(m_documentLoader->allowsDataURLsForMainFrame());
1749 applyShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToNewDocumentLoader(m_frame, loader, InitiatedByMainFrame::Unknown, m_documentLoader->shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToPropagate());
1750
1751 loader->setUserContentExtensionsEnabled(!options.contains(ReloadOption::DisableContentBlockers));
1752
1753 ResourceRequest& request = loader->request();
1754
1755 // FIXME: We don't have a mechanism to revalidate the main resource without reloading at the moment.
1756 request.setCachePolicy(ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData);
1757
1758 addSameSiteInfoToRequestIfNeeded(request);
1759
1760 // If we're about to re-post, set up action so the application can warn the user.
1761 if (request.httpMethod() == "POST")
1762 loader->setTriggeringAction({ *m_frame.document(), request, InitiatedByMainFrame::Unknown, NavigationType::FormResubmitted });
1763
1764 loader->setOverrideEncoding(m_documentLoader->overrideEncoding());
1765
1766 auto frameLoadTypeForReloadOptions = [] (auto options) {
1767 if (options & ReloadOption::FromOrigin)
1768 return FrameLoadType::ReloadFromOrigin;
1769 if (options & ReloadOption::ExpiredOnly)
1770 return FrameLoadType::ReloadExpiredOnly;
1771 return FrameLoadType::Reload;
1772 };
1773
1774 loadWithDocumentLoader(loader.ptr(), frameLoadTypeForReloadOptions(options), { }, AllowNavigationToInvalidURL::Yes);
1775}
1776
1777void FrameLoader::stopAllLoaders(ClearProvisionalItem clearProvisionalItem, StopLoadingPolicy stopLoadingPolicy)
1778{
1779 if (m_frame.document() && m_frame.document()->backForwardCacheState() == Document::InBackForwardCache)
1780 return;
1781
1782 if (stopLoadingPolicy == StopLoadingPolicy::PreventDuringUnloadEvents && !isStopLoadingAllowed())
1783 return;
1784
1785 // If this method is called from within this method, infinite recursion can occur (3442218). Avoid this.
1786 if (m_inStopAllLoaders)
1787 return;
1788
1789 // This method might dispatch events.
1790 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread::isScriptAllowed());
1791
1792 // Calling stopLoading() on the provisional document loader can blow away
1793 // the frame from underneath.
1794 Ref<Frame> protect(m_frame);
1795
1796 m_inStopAllLoaders = true;
1797
1798 policyChecker().stopCheck();
1799
1800 // If no new load is in progress, we should clear the provisional item from history
1801 // before we call stopLoading.
1802 if (clearProvisionalItem == ClearProvisionalItem::Yes)
1803 history().setProvisionalItem(nullptr);
1804
1805 for (RefPtr<Frame> child = m_frame.tree().firstChild(); child; child = child->tree().nextSibling())
1806 child->loader().stopAllLoaders(clearProvisionalItem);
1807
1808 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "stopAllLoaders: m_provisionalDocumentLoader=%p, m_documentLoader=%p", m_provisionalDocumentLoader.get(), m_documentLoader.get());
1809
1810 if (m_provisionalDocumentLoader)
1811 m_provisionalDocumentLoader->stopLoading();
1812 if (m_documentLoader)
1813 m_documentLoader->stopLoading();
1814 if (m_frame.page() && !m_frame.page()->chrome().client().isSVGImageChromeClient())
1815 platformStrategies()->loaderStrategy()->browsingContextRemoved(frame());
1816
1817 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "stopAllLoaders: Clearing provisional document loader (m_provisionalDocumentLoader=%p)", m_provisionalDocumentLoader.get());
1818 setProvisionalDocumentLoader(nullptr);
1819
1820 m_inStopAllLoaders = false;
1821}
1822
1823void FrameLoader::stopForBackForwardCache()
1824{
1825 // Stop provisional loads in subframes (The one in the main frame is about to be committed).
1826 if (!m_frame.isMainFrame()) {
1827 if (m_provisionalDocumentLoader)
1828 m_provisionalDocumentLoader->stopLoading();
1829 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "stopForBackForwardCache: Clearing provisional document loader (m_provisionalDocumentLoader=%p)", m_provisionalDocumentLoader.get());
1830 setProvisionalDocumentLoader(nullptr);
1831 }
1832
1833 // Stop current loads.
1834 if (m_documentLoader)
1835 m_documentLoader->stopLoading();
1836
1837 for (RefPtr<Frame> child = m_frame.tree().firstChild(); child; child = child->tree().nextSibling())
1838 child->loader().stopForBackForwardCache();
1839
1840 // We cancel pending navigations & policy checks *after* cancelling loads because cancelling loads might end up
1841 // running script, which could schedule new navigations.
1842 policyChecker().stopCheck();
1843 m_frame.navigationScheduler().cancel();
1844}

1900void FrameLoader::setDocumentLoader(DocumentLoader* loader)
1901{
1902 if (loader == m_documentLoader)
1903 return;
1904
1905 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "setDocumentLoader: Setting document loader to %p (was %p)", loader, m_documentLoader.get());
1906
1907 RELEASE_ASSERT(!loader || loader->frameLoader() == this);
1908
1909 m_client->prepareForDataSourceReplacement();
1910 detachChildren();
1911
1912 // detachChildren() can trigger this frame's unload event, and therefore
1913 // script can run and do just about anything. For example, an unload event that calls
1914 // document.write("") on its parent frame can lead to a recursive detachChildren()
1915 // invocation for this frame. In that case, we can end up at this point with a
1916 // loader that hasn't been deleted but has been detached from its frame. Such a
1917 // DocumentLoader has been sufficiently detached that we'll end up in an inconsistent
1918 // state if we try to use it.
1919 if (loader && !loader->frame())
1920 return;
1921
1922 if (m_documentLoader)
1923 m_documentLoader->detachFromFrame();
1924
1925 m_documentLoader = loader;
1926}

1928void FrameLoader::setPolicyDocumentLoader(DocumentLoader* loader)
1929{
1930 if (m_policyDocumentLoader == loader)
1931 return;
1932
1933 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "setPolicyDocumentLoader: Setting policy document loader to %p (was %p)", loader, m_policyDocumentLoader.get());
1934
1935 if (loader)
1936 loader->attachToFrame(m_frame);
1937 if (m_policyDocumentLoader
1938 && m_policyDocumentLoader != m_provisionalDocumentLoader
1939 && m_policyDocumentLoader != m_documentLoader)
1940 m_policyDocumentLoader->detachFromFrame();
1941
1942 m_policyDocumentLoader = loader;
1943}

1949

1962{

1986
1987void FrameLoader::commitProvisionalLoad()
1988{
1989 RefPtr<DocumentLoader> pdl = m_provisionalDocumentLoader;
1990 Ref<Frame> protect(m_frame);
1991
1992 std::unique_ptr<CachedPage> cachedPage;
1993 if (m_loadingFromCachedPage && history().provisionalItem())
1994 cachedPage = BackForwardCache::singleton().take(*history().provisionalItem(), m_frame.page());
1995
1996 LOG(BackForwardCache, "WebCoreLoading %s: About to commit provisional load from previous URL '%s' to new URL '%s' with cached page %p", m_frame.tree().uniqueName().string().utf8().data(),
1997 m_frame.document() ? m_frame.document()->url().stringCenterEllipsizedToLength().utf8().data() : "",
1998 pdl ? pdl->url().stringCenterEllipsizedToLength().utf8().data() : "<no provisional DocumentLoader>", cachedPage.get());
1999
2000 if (auto document = makeRefPtr(m_frame.document())) {
2001 // In the case where we're restoring from a cached page, our document will not
2002 // be connected to its frame yet, so the following call with be a no-op. We will
2003 // attempt to confirm any active composition once again in this scenario after we
2004 // finish restoring from the cached page.
2005 document->editor().confirmOrCancelCompositionAndNotifyClient();
2006 }
2007
2008 if (!m_frame.tree().parent() && history().currentItem() && history().currentItem() != history().provisionalItem()) {
2009 // Check to see if we need to cache the page we are navigating away from into the back/forward cache.
2010 // We are doing this here because we know for sure that a new page is about to be loaded.
2011 BackForwardCache::singleton().addIfCacheable(*history().currentItem(), m_frame.page());
2012
2013 WebCore::jettisonExpensiveObjectsOnTopLevelNavigation();
2014 }
2015
2016 if (m_loadType != FrameLoadType::Replace)
2017 closeOldDataSources();
2018
2019 if (!cachedPage && !m_stateMachine.creatingInitialEmptyDocument())
2020 m_client->makeRepresentation(pdl.get());
2021
2022 transitionToCommitted(cachedPage.get());
2023
2024 if (pdl && m_documentLoader) {
2025 // Check if the destination page is allowed to access the previous page's timing information.
2026 Ref<SecurityOrigin> securityOrigin(SecurityOrigin::create(pdl->request().url()));
2027 m_documentLoader->timing().setHasSameOriginAsPreviousDocument(securityOrigin.get().canRequest(m_previousURL));
2028 }
2029
2030 // Call clientRedirectCancelledOrFinished() here so that the frame load delegate is notified that the redirect's
2031 // status has changed, if there was a redirect. The frame load delegate may have saved some state about
2032 // the redirect in its -webView:willPerformClientRedirectToURL:delay:fireDate:forFrame:. Since we are
2033 // just about to commit a new page, there cannot possibly be a pending redirect at this point.
2034 if (m_sentRedirectNotification)
2035 clientRedirectCancelledOrFinished(NewLoadInProgress::No);
2036
2037 if (cachedPage && cachedPage->document()) {
2038#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2039 // FIXME: CachedPage::restore() would dispatch viewport change notification. However UIKit expects load
2040 // commit to happen before any changes to viewport arguments and dealing with this there is difficult.
2041 m_frame.page()->chrome().setDispatchViewportDataDidChangeSuppressed(true);
2042#endif
2043 willRestoreFromCachedPage();
2044
2045 // Start request for the main resource and dispatch didReceiveResponse before the load is committed for
2046 // consistency with all other loads. See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=150927.
2047 ResourceError mainResouceError;
2048 unsigned long mainResourceIdentifier;
2049 ResourceRequest mainResourceRequest(cachedPage->documentLoader()->request());
2050 requestFromDelegate(mainResourceRequest, mainResourceIdentifier, mainResouceError);
2051 notifier().dispatchDidReceiveResponse(cachedPage->documentLoader(), mainResourceIdentifier, cachedPage->documentLoader()->response());
2052
2053 auto hasInsecureContent = cachedPage->cachedMainFrame()->hasInsecureContent();
2054 auto usedLegacyTLS = cachedPage->cachedMainFrame()->usedLegacyTLS();
2055
2056 dispatchDidCommitLoad(hasInsecureContent, usedLegacyTLS);
2057
2058 // FIXME: This API should be turned around so that we ground CachedPage into the Page.
2059 cachedPage->restore(*m_frame.page());
2060
2061#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2062 m_frame.page()->chrome().setDispatchViewportDataDidChangeSuppressed(false);
2063 m_frame.page()->chrome().dispatchViewportPropertiesDidChange(m_frame.page()->viewportArguments());
2064#endif
2065 m_frame.page()->chrome().dispatchDisabledAdaptationsDidChange(m_frame.page()->disabledAdaptations());
2066
2067 auto& title = m_documentLoader->title();
2068 if (!title.string.isNull())
2069 m_client->dispatchDidReceiveTitle(title);
2070
2071 // Send remaining notifications for the main resource.
2072 notifier().sendRemainingDelegateMessages(m_documentLoader.get(), mainResourceIdentifier, mainResourceRequest, ResourceResponse(),
2073 nullptr, static_cast<int>(m_documentLoader->response().expectedContentLength()), 0, mainResouceError);
2074
2075 Vector<Ref<Frame>> targetFrames;
2076 targetFrames.append(m_frame);
2077 for (auto* child = m_frame.tree().firstChild(); child; child = child->tree().traverseNext(&m_frame))
2078 targetFrames.append(*child);
2079
2080 for (auto& frame : targetFrames)
2081 frame->loader().checkCompleted();
2082 } else
2083 didOpenURL();
2084
2085 if (auto document = makeRefPtr(m_frame.document()))
2086 document->editor().confirmOrCancelCompositionAndNotifyClient();
2087
2088 LOG(Loading, "WebCoreLoading %s: Finished committing provisional load to URL %s", m_frame.tree().uniqueName().string().utf8().data(),
2089 m_frame.document() ? m_frame.document()->url().stringCenterEllipsizedToLength().utf8().data() : "");
2090
2091 if (m_loadType == FrameLoadType::Standard && m_documentLoader && m_documentLoader->isClientRedirect())
2092 history().updateForClientRedirect();
2093
2094 if (m_loadingFromCachedPage) {
2095 // Note, didReceiveDocType is expected to be called for cached pages. See <rdar://problem/5906758> for more details.
2096 if (auto* page = m_frame.page())
2097 page->chrome().didReceiveDocType(m_frame);
2098 m_frame.document()->resume(ReasonForSuspension::BackForwardCache);
2099
2100 // Force a layout to update view size and thereby update scrollbars.
2101#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2102 if (!m_client->forceLayoutOnRestoreFromBackForwardCache())
2103 m_frame.view()->forceLayout();
2104#else
2105 m_frame.view()->forceLayout();
2106#endif
2107
2108 // Main resource delegates were already sent, so we skip the first response here.
2109 for (unsigned i = 1; i < m_documentLoader->responses().size(); ++i) {
2110 const auto& response = m_documentLoader->responses()[i];
2111 // FIXME: If the WebKit client changes or cancels the request, this is not respected.
2112 ResourceError error;
2113 unsigned long identifier;
2114 ResourceRequest request(response.url());
2115 requestFromDelegate(request, identifier, error);
2116 // FIXME: If we get a resource with more than 2B bytes, this code won't do the right thing.
2117 // However, with today's computers and networking speeds, this won't happen in practice.
2118 // Could be an issue with a giant local file.
2119 notifier().sendRemainingDelegateMessages(m_documentLoader.get(), identifier, request, response, 0, static_cast<int>(response.expectedContentLength()), 0, error);
2120 }
2121
2122 // FIXME: Why only this frame and not parent frames?
2123 checkLoadCompleteForThisFrame();
2124 }
2125}
2126
2127void FrameLoader::transitionToCommitted(CachedPage* cachedPage)
2128{
2129 ASSERT(m_client->hasWebView());
2130 ASSERT(m_state == FrameState::Provisional);
2131
2132 if (m_state != FrameState::Provisional)
2133 return;
2134
2135 if (FrameView* view = m_frame.view()) {
2136 if (ScrollAnimator* scrollAnimator = view->existingScrollAnimator())
2137 scrollAnimator->cancelAnimations();
2138 }
2139
2140 m_client->setCopiesOnScroll();
2141 history().updateForCommit();
2142
2143 // The call to closeURL() invokes the unload event handler, which can execute arbitrary
2144 // JavaScript. If the script initiates a new load, we need to abandon the current load,
2145 // or the two will stomp each other.
2146 auto originalProvisionalDocumentLoader = m_provisionalDocumentLoader;
2147 if (m_documentLoader)
2148 closeURL();
2149 if (originalProvisionalDocumentLoader != m_provisionalDocumentLoader)
2150 return;
2151
2152 if (m_documentLoader)
2153 m_documentLoader->stopLoadingSubresources();
2154 if (m_documentLoader)
2155 m_documentLoader->stopLoadingPlugIns();
2156
2157 // Setting our document loader invokes the unload event handler of our child frames.
2158 // Script can do anything. If the script initiates a new load, we need to abandon the
2159 // current load or the two will stomp each other.
2160 setDocumentLoader(m_provisionalDocumentLoader.get());
2161 if (originalProvisionalDocumentLoader != m_provisionalDocumentLoader)
2162 return;
2163 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "transitionToCommitted: Clearing provisional document loader (m_provisionalDocumentLoader=%p)", m_provisionalDocumentLoader.get());
2164 setProvisionalDocumentLoader(nullptr);
2165
2166 // Nothing else can interrupt this commit - set the Provisional->Committed transition in stone
2167 setState(FrameState::CommittedPage);
2168
2169 // Handle adding the URL to the back/forward list.
2170 auto documentLoader = m_documentLoader;
2171
2172 switch (m_loadType) {
2173 case FrameLoadType::Forward:
2174 case FrameLoadType::Back:
2175 case FrameLoadType::IndexedBackForward:
2176 if (m_frame.page()) {
2177 // If the first load within a frame is a navigation within a back/forward list that was attached
2178 // without any of the items being loaded then we need to update the history in a similar manner as
2179 // for a standard load with the exception of updating the back/forward list (<rdar://problem/8091103>).
2180 if (!m_stateMachine.committedFirstRealDocumentLoad() && m_frame.isMainFrame())
2181 history().updateForStandardLoad(HistoryController::UpdateAllExceptBackForwardList);
2182
2183 history().updateForBackForwardNavigation();
2184
2185 // For cached pages, CachedFrame::restore will take care of firing the popstate event with the history item's state object
2186 if (history().currentItem() && !cachedPage)
2187 m_pendingStateObject = history().currentItem()->stateObject();
2188
2189 // Create a document view for this document, or used the cached view.
2190 if (cachedPage) {
2191 ASSERT(cachedPage->documentLoader());
2192 cachedPage->documentLoader()->attachToFrame(m_frame);
2193 m_client->transitionToCommittedFromCachedFrame(cachedPage->cachedMainFrame());
2194 } else
2195 m_client->transitionToCommittedForNewPage();
2196 }
2197 break;
2198
2199 case FrameLoadType::Reload:
2200 case FrameLoadType::ReloadFromOrigin:
2201 case FrameLoadType::ReloadExpiredOnly:
2202 case FrameLoadType::Same:
2203 case FrameLoadType::Replace:
2204 history().updateForReload();
2205 m_client->transitionToCommittedForNewPage();
2206 break;
2207
2208 case FrameLoadType::Standard:
2209 history().updateForStandardLoad();
2210 if (m_frame.view())
2211 m_frame.view()->setScrollbarsSuppressed(true);
2212 m_client->transitionToCommittedForNewPage();
2213 break;
2214
2215 case FrameLoadType::RedirectWithLockedBackForwardList:
2216 history().updateForRedirectWithLockedBackForwardList();
2217 m_client->transitionToCommittedForNewPage();
2218 break;
2219 }
2220
2221 if (documentLoader)
2222 documentLoader->writer().setMIMEType(documentLoader->responseMIMEType());
2223
2224 if (m_stateMachine.creatingInitialEmptyDocument())
2225 return;
2226
2227 if (!m_stateMachine.committedFirstRealDocumentLoad())
2228 m_stateMachine.advanceTo(FrameLoaderStateMachine::DisplayingInitialEmptyDocumentPostCommit);
2229}
