2231void FrameLoader::clientRedirectCancelledOrFinished(NewLoadInProgress newLoadInProgress)
2232{
2233 // Note that -webView:didCancelClientRedirectForFrame: is called on the frame load delegate even if
2234 // the redirect succeeded. We should either rename this API, or add a new method, like
2235 // -webView:didFinishClientRedirectForFrame:
2236 m_client->dispatchDidCancelClientRedirect();
2237
2238 if (newLoadInProgress == NewLoadInProgress::No)
2239 m_quickRedirectComing = false;
2240
2241 m_sentRedirectNotification = false;
2242}
2243
2244void FrameLoader::clientRedirected(const URL& url, double seconds, WallTime fireDate, LockBackForwardList lockBackForwardList)
2245{
2246 m_client->dispatchWillPerformClientRedirect(url, seconds, fireDate, lockBackForwardList);
2247
2248 // Remember that we sent a redirect notification to the frame load delegate so that when we commit
2249 // the next provisional load, we can send a corresponding -webView:didCancelClientRedirectForFrame:
2250 m_sentRedirectNotification = true;
2251
2252 // If a "quick" redirect comes in, we set a special mode so we treat the next
2253 // load as part of the original navigation. If we don't have a document loader, we have
2254 // no "original" load on which to base a redirect, so we treat the redirect as a normal load.
2255 // Loads triggered by JavaScript form submissions never count as quick redirects.
2256 m_quickRedirectComing = (lockBackForwardList == LockBackForwardList::Yes || history().currentItemShouldBeReplaced()) && m_documentLoader && !m_isExecutingJavaScriptFormAction;
2257}
2258
2259bool FrameLoader::shouldReload(const URL& currentURL, const URL& destinationURL)
2260{
2261 // This function implements the rule: "Don't reload if navigating by fragment within
2262 // the same URL, but do reload if going to a new URL or to the same URL with no
2263 // fragment identifier at all."
2264 if (!destinationURL.hasFragmentIdentifier())
2265 return true;
2266 return !equalIgnoringFragmentIdentifier(currentURL, destinationURL);
2267}

2274 for (Frame* child = m_frame.tree().firstChild(); child; child = child->tree().nextSibling())

2283void FrameLoader::willRestoreFromCachedPage()
2284{
2285 ASSERT(!m_frame.tree().parent());
2286 ASSERT(m_frame.page());
2287 ASSERT(m_frame.isMainFrame());
2288
2289 m_frame.navigationScheduler().cancel();
2290
2291 // We still have to close the previous part page.
2292 closeURL();
2293
2294 // Delete old status bar messages (if it _was_ activated on last URL).
2295 if (m_frame.script().canExecuteScripts(NotAboutToExecuteScript)) {

2302void FrameLoader::open(CachedFrameBase& cachedFrame)
2303{
2304 // Don't re-emit the load event.
2305 m_didCallImplicitClose = true;
2306
2307 URL url = cachedFrame.url();
2308
2309 // FIXME: I suspect this block of code doesn't do anything.
2310 if (url.protocolIsInHTTPFamily() && !url.host().isEmpty() && url.path().isEmpty())
2311 url.setPath("/");
2312
2313 started();
2314 auto document = makeRef(*cachedFrame.document());
2315 ASSERT(document->domWindow());
2316
2317 clear(document.ptr(), true, true, cachedFrame.isMainFrame());
2318
2319 document->attachToCachedFrame(cachedFrame);
2320 document->setBackForwardCacheState(Document::NotInBackForwardCache);
2321
2322 m_needsClear = true;
2323 m_isComplete = false;
2324 m_didCallImplicitClose = false;
2325 setOutgoingReferrer(url);
2326
2327 FrameView* view = cachedFrame.view();
2328
2329 // When navigating to a CachedFrame its FrameView should never be null. If it is we'll crash in creative ways downstream.
2330 ASSERT(view);
2331 view->setWasScrolledByUser(false);
2332
2333 std::optional<IntRect> previousViewFrameRect = m_frame.view() ? m_frame.view()->frameRect() : std::optional<IntRect>(std::nullopt);
2334 m_frame.setView(view);
2335
2336 // Use the previous ScrollView's frame rect.
2337 if (previousViewFrameRect)
2338 view->setFrameRect(previousViewFrameRect.value());
2339
2340
2341 // Setting the document builds the render tree and runs post style resolution callbacks that can do anything,
2342 // including loading a child frame before its been re-attached to the frame tree as part of this restore.
2343 // For example, the HTML object element may load its content into a frame in a post style resolution callback.
2344 Style::PostResolutionCallbackDisabler disabler(document.get());
2345 WidgetHierarchyUpdatesSuspensionScope suspendWidgetHierarchyUpdates;
2346 NavigationDisabler disableNavigation { &m_frame };
2347
2348 m_frame.setDocument(document.copyRef());
2349
2350 document->domWindow()->resumeFromBackForwardCache();
2351
2352 updateFirstPartyForCookies();
2353
2354 cachedFrame.restore();
2355}

2367bool FrameLoader::subframeIsLoading() const
2368{
2369 // It's most likely that the last added frame is the last to load so we walk backwards.
2370 for (Frame* child = m_frame.tree().lastChild(); child; child = child->tree().previousSibling()) {
2371 FrameLoader& childLoader = child->loader();
2372 DocumentLoader* documentLoader = childLoader.documentLoader();
2373 if (documentLoader && documentLoader->isLoadingInAPISense())
2374 return true;
2375 documentLoader = childLoader.provisionalDocumentLoader();
2376 if (documentLoader && documentLoader->isLoadingInAPISense())
2377 return true;
2378 documentLoader = childLoader.policyDocumentLoader();
2379 if (documentLoader)
2380 return true;
2381 }
2382 return false;
2383}

2394
2395CachePolicy FrameLoader::subresourceCachePolicy(const URL& url) const
2396{
2397 if (Page* page = m_frame.page()) {
2398 if (page->isResourceCachingDisabledByWebInspector())
2399 return CachePolicy::Reload;
2400 }
2401
2402 if (m_isComplete)
2403 return CachePolicy::Verify;
2404
2405 if (m_loadType == FrameLoadType::ReloadFromOrigin)
2406 return CachePolicy::Reload;
2407
2408 if (Frame* parentFrame = m_frame.tree().parent()) {
2409 CachePolicy parentCachePolicy = parentFrame->loader().subresourceCachePolicy(url);
2410 if (parentCachePolicy != CachePolicy::Verify)
2411 return parentCachePolicy;
2412 }
2413
2414 switch (m_loadType) {
2415 case FrameLoadType::Reload:
2416 return CachePolicy::Revalidate;
2417 case FrameLoadType::Back:
2418 case FrameLoadType::Forward:
2419 case FrameLoadType::IndexedBackForward:
2420 return CachePolicy::HistoryBuffer;
2421 case FrameLoadType::ReloadFromOrigin:
2422 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED(); // Already handled above.
2423 return CachePolicy::Reload;
2424 case FrameLoadType::RedirectWithLockedBackForwardList:
2425 case FrameLoadType::Replace:
2426 case FrameLoadType::Same:
2427 case FrameLoadType::Standard:
2428 return CachePolicy::Verify;
2429 case FrameLoadType::ReloadExpiredOnly:
2430 // We know about expiration for HTTP and data. Do a normal reload otherwise.
2431 if (!url.protocolIsInHTTPFamily() && !url.protocolIsData())
2432 return CachePolicy::Reload;
2433 return CachePolicy::Verify;
2434 }
2435
2436 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2437 return CachePolicy::Verify;
2438}
2439
2440void FrameLoader::dispatchDidFailProvisionalLoad(DocumentLoader& provisionalDocumentLoader, const ResourceError& error)
2441{
2442 m_provisionalLoadErrorBeingHandledURL = provisionalDocumentLoader.url();
2443
2444#if ENABLE(CONTENT_FILTERING)
2445 auto contentFilter = provisionalDocumentLoader.contentFilter();
2446 auto contentFilterWillContinueLoading = false;
2447#endif
2448
2449 auto willContinueLoading = WillContinueLoading::No;
2450 if (history().provisionalItem())
2451 willContinueLoading = WillContinueLoading::Yes;
2452#if ENABLE(CONTENT_FILTERING)
2453 if (contentFilter && contentFilter->willHandleProvisionalLoadFailure(error)) {
2454 willContinueLoading = WillContinueLoading::Yes;
2455 contentFilterWillContinueLoading = true;
2456 }
2457#endif
2458
2459 m_client->dispatchDidFailProvisionalLoad(error, willContinueLoading);
2460
2461#if ENABLE(CONTENT_FILTERING)
2462 if (contentFilterWillContinueLoading)
2463 contentFilter->handleProvisionalLoadFailure(error);
2464#endif
2465
2466 m_provisionalLoadErrorBeingHandledURL = { };
2467}
2468
2469void FrameLoader::checkLoadCompleteForThisFrame()
2470{
2471 ASSERT(m_client->hasWebView());
2472
2473 // FIXME: Should this check be done in checkLoadComplete instead of here?
2474 // FIXME: Why does this one check need to be repeated here, and not the many others from checkCompleted?
2475 if (m_frame.document()->isDelayingLoadEvent())
2476 return;
2477
2478 switch (m_state) {
2479 case FrameState::Provisional: {
2480 // FIXME: Prohibiting any provisional load failures from being sent to clients
2481 // while handling provisional load failures is too heavy. For example, the current
2482 // load will fail to cancel another ongoing load. That might prevent clients' page
2483 // load state being handled properly.
2484 if (!m_provisionalLoadErrorBeingHandledURL.isEmpty())
2485 return;
2486
2487 RefPtr<DocumentLoader> protector = m_provisionalDocumentLoader;
2488 if (!protector)
2489 return;
2490
2491 // If we've received any errors we may be stuck in the provisional state and actually complete.
2492 const ResourceError& error = protector->mainDocumentError();
2493 if (error.isNull())
2494 return;
2495
2496 // Check all children first.
2497 RefPtr<HistoryItem> item;
2498 if (Page* page = m_frame.page()) {
2499 if (isBackForwardLoadType(loadType())) {
2500 // Reset the back forward list to the last committed history item at the top level.
2501 item = page->mainFrame().loader().history().currentItem();
2502 }
2503 }
2504
2505 // Only reset if we aren't already going to a new provisional item.
2506 bool shouldReset = !history().provisionalItem();
2507 if (!protector->isLoadingInAPISense() || protector->isStopping()) {
2508 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "checkLoadCompleteForThisFrame: Failed provisional load (isTimeout = %d, isCancellation = %d, errorCode = %d)", error.isTimeout(), error.isCancellation(), error.errorCode());
2509
2510 dispatchDidFailProvisionalLoad(*protector, error);
2511 ASSERT(!protector->isLoading());
2512
2513 // If we're in the middle of loading multipart data, we need to restore the document loader.
2514 if (isReplacing() && !m_documentLoader.get())
2515 setDocumentLoader(m_provisionalDocumentLoader.get());
2516
2517 // Finish resetting the load state, but only if another load hasn't been started by the
2518 // delegate callback.
2519 if (protector == m_provisionalDocumentLoader)
2520 clearProvisionalLoad();
2521 else if (activeDocumentLoader()) {
2522 URL unreachableURL = activeDocumentLoader()->unreachableURL();
2523 if (!unreachableURL.isEmpty() && unreachableURL == protector->request().url())
2524 shouldReset = false;
2525 }
2526 }
2527 if (shouldReset && item) {
2528 if (Page* page = m_frame.page())
2529 page->backForward().setCurrentItem(*item);
2530 }
2531 return;
2532 }
2533
2534 case FrameState::CommittedPage: {
2535 if (!m_documentLoader)
2536 return;
2537 if (m_documentLoader->isLoadingInAPISense() && !m_documentLoader->isStopping() && !m_checkingLoadCompleteForDetachment)
2538 return;
2539
2540 setState(FrameState::Complete);
2541
2542 // FIXME: Is this subsequent work important if we already navigated away?
2543 // Maybe there are bugs because of that, or extra work we can skip because
2544 // the new page is ready.
2545
2546 m_client->forceLayoutForNonHTML();
2547
2548 // If the user had a scroll point, scroll to it, overriding the anchor point if any.
2549 if (m_frame.page()) {
2550 if (isBackForwardLoadType(m_loadType) || isReload(m_loadType))
2551 history().restoreScrollPositionAndViewState();
2552 }
2553
2554 if (m_stateMachine.creatingInitialEmptyDocument() || !m_stateMachine.committedFirstRealDocumentLoad())
2555 return;
2556
2557 m_progressTracker->progressCompleted();
2558 Page* page = m_frame.page();
2559 if (page) {
2560 if (m_frame.isMainFrame()) {
2561 tracePoint(MainResourceLoadDidEnd);
2562 page->didFinishLoad();
2563 }
2564 }
2565
2566 if (auto domWindow = makeRefPtr(m_frame.document() ? m_frame.document()->domWindow() : nullptr))
2567 domWindow->performance().scheduleNavigationObservationTaskIfNeeded();
2568
2569 const ResourceError& error = m_documentLoader->mainDocumentError();
2570
2571 AXObjectCache::AXLoadingEvent loadingEvent;
2572 if (!error.isNull()) {
2573 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "checkLoadCompleteForThisFrame: Finished frame load with error (isTimeout = %d, isCancellation = %d, errorCode = %d)", error.isTimeout(), error.isCancellation(), error.errorCode());
2574 m_client->dispatchDidFailLoad(error);
2575 loadingEvent = AXObjectCache::AXLoadingFailed;
2576 } else {
2577 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "checkLoadCompleteForThisFrame: Finished frame load");
2578#if ENABLE(DATA_DETECTION)
2579 auto document = m_frame.document();
2580 auto types = OptionSet<DataDetectorType> { m_frame.settings().dataDetectorTypes() };
2581 if (document && types) {
2582 auto documentLevelResults = retainPtr(DataDetection::detectContentInRange(makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(*document), types, m_client->dataDetectionContext()));
2583 m_frame.dataDetectionResults().setDocumentLevelResults(documentLevelResults.get());
2584 if (m_frame.isMainFrame())
2585 m_client->dispatchDidFinishDataDetection(documentLevelResults.get());
2586 }
2587#endif
2588 m_client->dispatchDidFinishLoad();
2589 loadingEvent = AXObjectCache::AXLoadingFinished;
2590 }
2591
2592 // Notify accessibility.
2593 if (auto* document = m_frame.document()) {
2594 if (AXObjectCache* cache = document->existingAXObjectCache())
2595 cache->frameLoadingEventNotification(&m_frame, loadingEvent);
2596 }
2597
2598 // The above calls to dispatchDidFinishLoad() might have detached the Frame
2599 // from its Page and also might have caused Page to be deleted.
2600 // Don't assume 'page' is still available to use.
2601 if (m_frame.isMainFrame() && m_frame.page()) {
2602 ASSERT(&m_frame.page()->mainFrame() == &m_frame);
2603 m_frame.page()->diagnosticLoggingClient().logDiagnosticMessageWithResult(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::pageLoadedKey(), emptyString(), error.isNull() ? DiagnosticLoggingResultPass : DiagnosticLoggingResultFail, ShouldSample::Yes);
2604 }
2605
2606 return;
2607 }
2608
2609 case FrameState::Complete:
2610 m_loadType = FrameLoadType::Standard;
2611 frameLoadCompleted();
2612 return;
2613 }
2614
2615 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2616}

2618void FrameLoader::setOriginalURLForDownloadRequest(ResourceRequest& request)
2619{
2620 // FIXME: Rename firstPartyForCookies back to mainDocumentURL. It was a mistake to think that it was only used for cookies.
2621 // The originalURL is defined as the URL of the page where the download was initiated.
2622 URL originalURL;
2623 auto* initiator = m_frame.document();
2624 if (initiator) {
2625 originalURL = initiator->firstPartyForCookies();
2626 // If there is no main document URL, it means that this document is newly opened and just for download purpose.
2627 // In this case, we need to set the originalURL to this document's opener's main document URL.
2628 if (originalURL.isEmpty() && opener() && opener()->document()) {
2629 originalURL = opener()->document()->firstPartyForCookies();
2630 initiator = opener()->document();
2631 }
2632 }
2633 // If the originalURL is the same as the requested URL, we are processing a download
2634 // initiated directly without a page and do not need to specify the originalURL.
2635 if (originalURL == request.url())
2636 request.setFirstPartyForCookies(URL());
2637 else
2638 request.setFirstPartyForCookies(originalURL);
2639 addSameSiteInfoToRequestIfNeeded(request, initiator);
2640}

2685void FrameLoader::detachChildren()
2686{
2687 // detachChildren() will fire the unload event in each subframe and the
2688 // HTML specification states that the parent document's ignore-opens-during-unload counter while
2689 // this event is being fired in its subframes:
2690 // https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/browsers.html#unload-a-document
2691 IgnoreOpensDuringUnloadCountIncrementer ignoreOpensDuringUnloadCountIncrementer(m_frame.document());
2692
2693 // detachChildren() will fire the unload event in each subframe and the
2694 // HTML specification states that navigations should be prevented during the prompt to unload algorithm:
2695 // https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/browsing-the-web.html#navigate
2696 std::unique_ptr<NavigationDisabler> navigationDisabler;
2697 if (m_frame.isMainFrame())
2698 navigationDisabler = makeUnique<NavigationDisabler>(&m_frame);
2699
2700 // Any subframe inserted by unload event handlers executed in the loop below will not get unloaded
2701 // because we create a copy of the subframes list before looping. Therefore, it would be unsafe to
2702 // allow loading of subframes at this point.
2703 SubframeLoadingDisabler subframeLoadingDisabler(m_frame.document());
2704
2705 Vector<Ref<Frame>, 16> childrenToDetach;
2706 childrenToDetach.reserveInitialCapacity(m_frame.tree().childCount());
2707 for (Frame* child = m_frame.tree().lastChild(); child; child = child->tree().previousSibling())
2708 childrenToDetach.uncheckedAppend(*child);
2709 for (auto& child : childrenToDetach)
2710 child->loader().detachFromParent();
2711}

2715 child.tree().detachFromParent();
2716
2717 child.setView(nullptr);
2718 child.willDetachPage();
2719 child.detachFromPage();
2720
2721 m_frame.tree().removeChild(child);
2722}

2724// Called every time a resource is completely loaded or an error is received.
2725void FrameLoader::checkLoadComplete()
2726{
2727 m_shouldCallCheckLoadComplete = false;
2728
2729 if (!m_frame.page())
2730 return;
2731
2732 ASSERT(m_client->hasWebView());
2733
2734 // FIXME: Always traversing the entire frame tree is a bit inefficient, but
2735 // is currently needed in order to null out the previous history item for all frames.
2736 Vector<Ref<Frame>, 16> frames;
2737 for (Frame* frame = &m_frame.mainFrame(); frame; frame = frame->tree().traverseNext())
2738 frames.append(*frame);
2739
2740 // To process children before their parents, iterate the vector backwards.
2741 for (auto frame = frames.rbegin(); frame != frames.rend(); ++frame) {
2742 if ((*frame)->page())
2743 (*frame)->loader().checkLoadCompleteForThisFrame();
2744 }
2745}

2754 count += frame->document()->cachedResourceLoader().requestCount();
2755 return count;

2795void FrameLoader::frameDetached()
2796{
2797 // Calling stopAllLoadersAndCheckCompleteness() can cause the frame to be deallocated, including the frame loader.
2798 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
2799
2800 if (m_checkTimer.isActive()) {
2801 m_checkTimer.stop();
2802 checkCompletenessNow();
2803 }
2804
2805 if (m_frame.document()->backForwardCacheState() != Document::InBackForwardCache) {
2806 stopAllLoadersAndCheckCompleteness();
2807 m_frame.document()->stopActiveDOMObjects();
2808 }
2809
2810 detachFromParent();
2811}
2812
2813void FrameLoader::detachFromParent()
2814{
2815 // Calling stopAllLoaders() can cause the frame to be deallocated, including the frame loader.
2816 Ref<Frame> protect(m_frame);
2817
2818 closeURL();
2819 history().saveScrollPositionAndViewStateToItem(history().currentItem());
2820 detachChildren();
2821 if (m_frame.document()->backForwardCacheState() != Document::InBackForwardCache) {
2822 // stopAllLoaders() needs to be called after detachChildren() if the document is not in the back/forward cache,
2823 // because detachedChildren() will trigger the unload event handlers of any child frames, and those event
2824 // handlers might start a new subresource load in this frame.
2825 stopAllLoaders(ClearProvisionalItem::Yes, StopLoadingPolicy::AlwaysStopLoading);
2826 }
2827
2828 InspectorInstrumentation::frameDetachedFromParent(m_frame);
2829
2830 detachViewsAndDocumentLoader();
2831
2832 m_progressTracker = nullptr;
2833
2834 if (Frame* parent = m_frame.tree().parent()) {
2835 parent->loader().closeAndRemoveChild(m_frame);
2836 parent->loader().scheduleCheckCompleted();
2837 parent->loader().scheduleCheckLoadComplete();
2838 } else {
2839 m_frame.setView(nullptr);
2840 m_frame.willDetachPage();
2841 m_frame.detachFromPage();
2842 }
2843}

2846{
2847 m_client->detachedFromParent2();
2848 setDocumentLoader(nullptr);
2849 m_client->detachedFromParent3();
2850}

2852ResourceRequestCachePolicy FrameLoader::defaultRequestCachingPolicy(const ResourceRequest& request, FrameLoadType loadType, bool isMainResource)
2853{
2854 if (m_overrideCachePolicyForTesting)
2855 return m_overrideCachePolicyForTesting.value();
2856
2857 if (isMainResource) {
2858 if (isReload(loadType) || request.isConditional())
2859 return ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData;
2860
2861 return ResourceRequestCachePolicy::UseProtocolCachePolicy;
2862 }
2863
2864 if (request.isConditional())
2865 return ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData;
2866
2867 auto* documentLoader = this->documentLoader();
2868 if (documentLoader && documentLoader->isLoadingInAPISense()) {
2869 // If we inherit cache policy from a main resource, we use the DocumentLoader's
2870 // original request cache policy for two reasons:
2871 // 1. For POST requests, we mutate the cache policy for the main resource,
2872 // but we do not want this to apply to subresources
2873 // 2. Delegates that modify the cache policy using willSendRequest: should
2874 // not affect any other resources. Such changes need to be done
2875 // per request.
2876 ResourceRequestCachePolicy mainDocumentOriginalCachePolicy = documentLoader->originalRequest().cachePolicy();
2877 // Back-forward navigations try to load main resource from cache only to avoid re-submitting form data, and start over (with a warning dialog) if that fails.
2878 // This policy is set on initial request too, but should not be inherited.
2879 return (mainDocumentOriginalCachePolicy == ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReturnCacheDataDontLoad) ? ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReturnCacheDataElseLoad : mainDocumentOriginalCachePolicy;
2880 }
2881
2882 return ResourceRequestCachePolicy::UseProtocolCachePolicy;
2883}
2884
2885void FrameLoader::updateRequestAndAddExtraFields(ResourceRequest& request, IsMainResource mainResource, FrameLoadType loadType, ShouldUpdateAppBoundValue shouldUpdate)
2886{
2887 // If the request came from a previous process due to process-swap-on-navigation then we should not modify the request.
2888 if (m_currentLoadContinuingState == LoadContinuingState::ContinuingWithRequest)
2889 return;
2890
2891 // Don't set the cookie policy URL if it's already been set.
2892 // But make sure to set it on all requests regardless of protocol, as it has significance beyond the cookie policy (<rdar://problem/6616664>).
2893 bool isMainResource = mainResource == IsMainResource::Yes;
2894 bool isMainFrameMainResource = isMainResource && m_frame.isMainFrame();
2895 if (request.firstPartyForCookies().isEmpty()) {
2896 if (isMainFrameMainResource)
2897 request.setFirstPartyForCookies(request.url());
2898 else if (Document* document = m_frame.document())
2899 request.setFirstPartyForCookies(document->firstPartyForCookies());
2900 }
2901
2902 if (request.isSameSiteUnspecified()) {
2903 auto* initiator = m_frame.document();
2904 if (isMainResource) {
2905 auto* ownerFrame = m_frame.tree().parent();
2906 if (!ownerFrame && m_stateMachine.isDisplayingInitialEmptyDocument())
2907 ownerFrame = m_opener.get();
2908 if (ownerFrame)
2909 initiator = ownerFrame->document();
2910 ASSERT(ownerFrame || m_frame.isMainFrame());
2911 }
2912 addSameSiteInfoToRequestIfNeeded(request, initiator);
2913 }
2914 request.setIsTopSite(isMainFrameMainResource);
2915
2916 Page* page = frame().page();
2917 bool hasSpecificCachePolicy = request.cachePolicy() != ResourceRequestCachePolicy::UseProtocolCachePolicy;
2918
2919 if (page && page->isResourceCachingDisabledByWebInspector()) {
2920 request.setCachePolicy(ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData);
2921 loadType = FrameLoadType::ReloadFromOrigin;
2922 } else if (!hasSpecificCachePolicy)
2923 request.setCachePolicy(defaultRequestCachingPolicy(request, loadType, isMainResource));
2924
2925 // The remaining modifications are only necessary for HTTP and HTTPS.
2926 if (!request.url().isEmpty() && !request.url().protocolIsInHTTPFamily())
2927 return;
2928
2929 if (!hasSpecificCachePolicy && request.cachePolicy() == ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData) {
2930 if (loadType == FrameLoadType::Reload)
2931 request.setHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::CacheControl, HTTPHeaderValues::maxAge0());
2932 else if (loadType == FrameLoadType::ReloadFromOrigin) {
2933 request.setHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::CacheControl, HTTPHeaderValues::noCache());
2934 request.setHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::Pragma, HTTPHeaderValues::noCache());
2935 }
2936 }
2937
2938 if (m_overrideResourceLoadPriorityForTesting)
2939 request.setPriority(m_overrideResourceLoadPriorityForTesting.value());
2940
2941 // Make sure we send the Origin header.
2942 addHTTPOriginIfNeeded(request, String());
2943
2944 applyUserAgentIfNeeded(request);
2945
2946 if (isMainResource)
2947 request.setHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::Accept, CachedResourceRequest::acceptHeaderValueFromType(CachedResource::Type::MainResource));
2948
2949 // Only set fallback array if it's still empty (later attempts may be incorrect, see bug 117818).
2950 if (request.responseContentDispositionEncodingFallbackArray().isEmpty()) {
2951 // Always try UTF-8. If that fails, try frame encoding (if any) and then the default.
2952 request.setResponseContentDispositionEncodingFallbackArray("UTF-8", m_frame.document()->encoding(), m_frame.settings().defaultTextEncodingName());
2953 }
2954
2955 if (shouldUpdate == ShouldUpdateAppBoundValue::Yes && m_frame.mainFrame().loader().documentLoader())
2956 request.setIsAppBound(m_frame.mainFrame().loader().documentLoader()->lastNavigationWasAppBound());
2957}

2959void FrameLoader::scheduleRefreshIfNeeded(Document& document, const String& content)
2960{
2961 double delay = 0;
2962 String urlString;
2963 if (parseMetaHTTPEquivRefresh(content, delay, urlString)) {
2964 auto completedURL = urlString.isEmpty() ? document.url() : document.completeURL(urlString);
2965 if (!completedURL.protocolIsJavaScript())
2966 m_frame.navigationScheduler().scheduleRedirect(document, delay, completedURL);
2967 else {
2968 String message = "Refused to refresh " + document.url().stringCenterEllipsizedToLength() + " to a javascript: URL";
2969 document.addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, message);
2970 }
2971 }

2973
2974void FrameLoader::addHTTPOriginIfNeeded(ResourceRequest& request, const String& origin)
2975{
2976 if (!request.httpOrigin().isEmpty())
2977 return; // Request already has an Origin header.
2978
2979 // Don't send an Origin header for GET or HEAD to avoid privacy issues.
2980 // For example, if an intranet page has a hyperlink to an external web
2981 // site, we don't want to include the Origin of the request because it
2982 // will leak the internal host name. Similar privacy concerns have lead
2983 // to the widespread suppression of the Referer header at the network
2984 // layer.
2985 if (request.httpMethod() == "GET" || request.httpMethod() == "HEAD")
2986 return;
2987
2988 // FIXME: take referrer-policy into account.
2989 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=209066
2990
2991 // For non-GET and non-HEAD methods, always send an Origin header so the
2992 // server knows we support this feature.
2993
2994 if (origin.isEmpty()) {
2995 // If we don't know what origin header to attach, we attach the value
2996 // for an empty origin.
2997 request.setHTTPOrigin(SecurityOrigin::createUnique()->toString());
2998 return;
2999 }
3000
3001 request.setHTTPOrigin(origin);
3002}
3003
3004// Implements the "'Same-site' and 'cross-site' Requests" algorithm from <https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-httpbis-cookie-same-site-00#section-2.1>.
3005// The algorithm is ammended to treat URLs that inherit their security origin from their owner (e.g. about:blank)
3006// as same-site. This matches the behavior of Chrome and Firefox.
3007void FrameLoader::addSameSiteInfoToRequestIfNeeded(ResourceRequest& request, const Document* initiator)
3008{
3009 if (!request.isSameSiteUnspecified())
3010 return;
3011 if (!initiator) {
3012 request.setIsSameSite(true);
3013 return;
3014 }
3015 if (SecurityPolicy::shouldInheritSecurityOriginFromOwner(request.url())) {
3016 request.setIsSameSite(true);
3017 return;
3018 }
3019 request.setIsSameSite(areRegistrableDomainsEqual(initiator->siteForCookies(), request.url()));
3020}
3021
3022void FrameLoader::loadPostRequest(FrameLoadRequest&& request, const String& referrer, FrameLoadType loadType, Event* event, RefPtr<FormState>&& formState, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
3023{
3024 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "loadPostRequest: frame load started");
3025
3026 String frameName = request.frameName();
3027 LockHistory lockHistory = request.lockHistory();
3028 AllowNavigationToInvalidURL allowNavigationToInvalidURL = request.allowNavigationToInvalidURL();
3029 NewFrameOpenerPolicy openerPolicy = request.newFrameOpenerPolicy();
3030
3031 const ResourceRequest& inRequest = request.resourceRequest();
3032 const URL& url = inRequest.url();
3033 const String& contentType = inRequest.httpContentType();
3034 String origin = inRequest.httpOrigin();
3035
3036 ResourceRequest workingResourceRequest(url);
3037
3038 if (!referrer.isEmpty())
3039 workingResourceRequest.setHTTPReferrer(referrer);
3040 workingResourceRequest.setHTTPOrigin(origin);
3041 workingResourceRequest.setHTTPMethod("POST");
3042 workingResourceRequest.setHTTPBody(inRequest.httpBody());
3043 workingResourceRequest.setHTTPContentType(contentType);
3044 updateRequestAndAddExtraFields(workingResourceRequest, IsMainResource::Yes, loadType);
3045
3046 if (Document* document = m_frame.document())
3047 document->contentSecurityPolicy()->upgradeInsecureRequestIfNeeded(workingResourceRequest, ContentSecurityPolicy::InsecureRequestType::Load);
3048
3049 NavigationAction action { request.requester(), workingResourceRequest, request.initiatedByMainFrame(), loadType, true, event, request.shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy(), { } };
3050 action.setLockHistory(lockHistory);
3051
3052 if (!frameName.isEmpty()) {
3053 // The search for a target frame is done earlier in the case of form submission.
3054 if (auto* targetFrame = formState ? nullptr : findFrameForNavigation(frameName)) {
3055 targetFrame->loader().loadWithNavigationAction(workingResourceRequest, WTFMove(action), loadType, WTFMove(formState), allowNavigationToInvalidURL, WTFMove(completionHandler));
3056 return;
3057 }
3058
3059 policyChecker().checkNewWindowPolicy(WTFMove(action), WTFMove(workingResourceRequest), WTFMove(formState), frameName, [this, allowNavigationToInvalidURL, openerPolicy, completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)] (const ResourceRequest& request, WeakPtr<FormState>&& formState, const String& frameName, const NavigationAction& action, ShouldContinuePolicyCheck shouldContinue) mutable {
3060 continueLoadAfterNewWindowPolicy(request, formState.get(), frameName, action, shouldContinue, allowNavigationToInvalidURL, openerPolicy);
3061 completionHandler();
3062 });
3063 return;
3064 }
3065
3066 // must grab this now, since this load may stop the previous load and clear this flag
3067 bool isRedirect = m_quickRedirectComing;
3068 loadWithNavigationAction(workingResourceRequest, WTFMove(action), loadType, WTFMove(formState), allowNavigationToInvalidURL, [this, isRedirect, protectedFrame = makeRef(m_frame), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)] () mutable {
3069 if (isRedirect) {
3070 m_quickRedirectComing = false;
3071 if (m_provisionalDocumentLoader)
3072 m_provisionalDocumentLoader->setIsClientRedirect(true);
3073 else if (m_policyDocumentLoader)
3074 m_policyDocumentLoader->setIsClientRedirect(true);
3075 }
3076 completionHandler();
3077 });
3078}

3138void FrameLoader::receivedMainResourceError(const ResourceError& error)
3139{
3140 // Retain because the stop may release the last reference to it.
3141 Ref<Frame> protect(m_frame);
3142
3143 RefPtr<DocumentLoader> loader = activeDocumentLoader();
3144 // FIXME: Don't want to do this if an entirely new load is going, so should check
3145 // that both data sources on the frame are either this or nil.
3146 stop();
3147 if (m_client->shouldFallBack(error)) {
3148 HTMLFrameOwnerElement* owner = m_frame.ownerElement();
3149 if (is<HTMLObjectElement>(owner))
3150 downcast<HTMLObjectElement>(*owner).renderFallbackContent();
3151 }
3152
3153 if (m_state == FrameState::Provisional && m_provisionalDocumentLoader) {
3154 if (m_submittedFormURL == m_provisionalDocumentLoader->originalRequestCopy().url())
3155 m_submittedFormURL = URL();
3156
3157 // We might have made a back/forward cache item, but now we're bailing out due to an error before we ever
3158 // transitioned to the new page (before WebFrameState == commit). The goal here is to restore any state
3159 // so that the existing view (that wenever got far enough to replace) can continue being used.
3160 history().invalidateCurrentItemCachedPage();
3161
3162 // Call clientRedirectCancelledOrFinished here so that the frame load delegate is notified that the redirect's
3163 // status has changed, if there was a redirect. The frame load delegate may have saved some state about
3164 // the redirect in its -webView:willPerformClientRedirectToURL:delay:fireDate:forFrame:. Since we are definitely
3165 // not going to use this provisional resource, as it was cancelled, notify the frame load delegate that the redirect
3166 // has ended.
3167 if (m_sentRedirectNotification)
3168 clientRedirectCancelledOrFinished(NewLoadInProgress::No);
3169 }
3170
3171 checkCompleted();
3172 if (m_frame.page())
3173 checkLoadComplete();
3174}

3198bool FrameLoader::shouldPerformFragmentNavigation(bool isFormSubmission, const String& httpMethod, FrameLoadType loadType, const URL& url)
3199{
3200 // We don't do this if we are submitting a form with method other than "GET", explicitly reloading,
3201 // currently displaying a frameset, or if the URL does not have a fragment.
3202 // These rules were originally based on what KHTML was doing in KHTMLPart::openURL.
3203
3204 // FIXME: What about load types other than Standard and Reload?
3205
3206 return (!isFormSubmission || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(httpMethod, "get"))
3207 && !isReload(loadType)
3208 && loadType != FrameLoadType::Same
3209 && m_frame.document()->backForwardCacheState() != Document::InBackForwardCache
3210 && !shouldReload(m_frame.document()->url(), url)
3211 // We don't want to just scroll if a link from within a
3212 // frameset is trying to reload the frameset into _top.
3213 && !m_frame.document()->isFrameSet();

3243bool FrameLoader::shouldClose()
3244{
3245 Page* page = m_frame.page();
3246 if (!page)
3247 return true;
3248 if (!page->chrome().canRunBeforeUnloadConfirmPanel())
3249 return true;
3250
3251 // Store all references to each subframe in advance since beforeunload's event handler may modify frame
3252 Vector<Ref<Frame>, 16> targetFrames;
3253 targetFrames.append(m_frame);
3254 for (Frame* child = m_frame.tree().firstChild(); child; child = child->tree().traverseNext(&m_frame))
3255 targetFrames.append(*child);
3256
3257 bool shouldClose = false;
3258 {
3259 NavigationDisabler navigationDisabler(&m_frame);
3260 IgnoreOpensDuringUnloadCountIncrementer ignoreOpensDuringUnloadCountIncrementer(m_frame.document());
3261 size_t i;
3262
3263 for (i = 0; i < targetFrames.size(); i++) {
3264 if (!targetFrames[i]->tree().isDescendantOf(&m_frame))
3265 continue;
3266 if (!targetFrames[i]->loader().dispatchBeforeUnloadEvent(page->chrome(), this))
3267 break;
3268 }
3269
3270 if (i == targetFrames.size())
3271 shouldClose = true;
3272 }
3273
3274 if (!shouldClose)
3275 m_submittedFormURL = URL();
3276
3277 m_currentNavigationHasShownBeforeUnloadConfirmPanel = false;
3278 return shouldClose;

3281void FrameLoader::dispatchUnloadEvents(UnloadEventPolicy unloadEventPolicy)
3282{
3283 if (!m_frame.document())
3284 return;
3285
3286 if (m_pageDismissalEventBeingDispatched != PageDismissalType::None)
3287 return;
3288
3289 // We store the frame's page in a local variable because the frame might get detached inside dispatchEvent.
3290 ForbidPromptsScope forbidPrompts(m_frame.page());
3291 ForbidSynchronousLoadsScope forbidSynchronousLoads(m_frame.page());
3292 IgnoreOpensDuringUnloadCountIncrementer ignoreOpensDuringUnloadCountIncrementer(m_frame.document());
3293
3294 if (m_didCallImplicitClose && !m_wasUnloadEventEmitted) {
3295 auto* currentFocusedElement = m_frame.document()->focusedElement();
3296 if (is<HTMLInputElement>(currentFocusedElement))
3297 downcast<HTMLInputElement>(*currentFocusedElement).endEditing();
3298 if (m_pageDismissalEventBeingDispatched == PageDismissalType::None) {
3299 if (unloadEventPolicy == UnloadEventPolicy::UnloadAndPageHide) {
3300 m_pageDismissalEventBeingDispatched = PageDismissalType::PageHide;
3301 m_frame.document()->domWindow()->dispatchEvent(PageTransitionEvent::create(eventNames().pagehideEvent, m_frame.document()->backForwardCacheState() == Document::AboutToEnterBackForwardCache), m_frame.document());
3302 }
3303
3304 // This takes care of firing the visibilitychange event and making sure the document is reported as hidden.
3305 m_frame.document()->setVisibilityHiddenDueToDismissal(true);
3306
3307 if (m_frame.document()->backForwardCacheState() == Document::NotInBackForwardCache) {
3308 Ref<Event> unloadEvent(Event::create(eventNames().unloadEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No));
3309 // The DocumentLoader (and thus its DocumentLoadTiming) might get destroyed
3310 // while dispatching the event, so protect it to prevent writing the end
3311 // time into freed memory.
3312 RefPtr<DocumentLoader> documentLoader = m_provisionalDocumentLoader;
3313 auto* timing = documentLoader ? &documentLoader->timing() : nullptr;
3314 m_pageDismissalEventBeingDispatched = PageDismissalType::Unload;
3315 if (timing && !timing->unloadEventStart())
3316 timing->markUnloadEventStart();
3317 m_frame.document()->domWindow()->dispatchEvent(unloadEvent, m_frame.document());
3318 if (timing && !timing->unloadEventEnd())
3319 timing->markUnloadEventEnd();
3320 }
3321 }
3322 m_pageDismissalEventBeingDispatched = PageDismissalType::None;
3323 m_wasUnloadEventEmitted = true;
3324 }
3325
3326 // Dispatching the unload event could have made m_frame.document() null.
3327 if (!m_frame.document())
3328 return;
3329
3330 if (m_frame.document()->backForwardCacheState() != Document::NotInBackForwardCache)
3331 return;
3332
3333 // Don't remove event listeners from a transitional empty document (see bug 28716 for more information).
3334 bool keepEventListeners = m_stateMachine.isDisplayingInitialEmptyDocument() && m_provisionalDocumentLoader
3335 && m_frame.document()->isSecureTransitionTo(m_provisionalDocumentLoader->url());
3336
3337 if (!keepEventListeners)
3338 m_frame.document()->removeAllEventListeners();
3339}
3340
3341static bool shouldAskForNavigationConfirmation(Document& document, const BeforeUnloadEvent& event)
3342{
3343 // Confirmation dialog should not be displayed when the allow-modals flag is not set.
3344 if (document.isSandboxed(SandboxModals))
3345 return false;
3346
3347 bool userDidInteractWithPage = document.topDocument().userDidInteractWithPage();
3348 // Web pages can request we ask for confirmation before navigating by:
3349 // - Cancelling the BeforeUnloadEvent (modern way)
3350 // - Setting the returnValue attribute on the BeforeUnloadEvent to a non-empty string.
3351 // - Returning a non-empty string from the event handler, which is then set as returnValue
3352 // attribute on the BeforeUnloadEvent.
3353 return userDidInteractWithPage && (event.defaultPrevented() || !event.returnValue().isEmpty());
3354}
3355
3356bool FrameLoader::dispatchBeforeUnloadEvent(Chrome& chrome, FrameLoader* frameLoaderBeingNavigated)
3357{
3358 DOMWindow* domWindow = m_frame.document()->domWindow();
3359 if (!domWindow)
3360 return true;
3361
3362 RefPtr<Document> document = m_frame.document();
3363 if (!document->bodyOrFrameset())
3364 return true;
3365
3366 Ref<BeforeUnloadEvent> beforeUnloadEvent = BeforeUnloadEvent::create();
3367
3368 {
3369 SetForScope<PageDismissalType> change(m_pageDismissalEventBeingDispatched, PageDismissalType::BeforeUnload);
3370 ForbidPromptsScope forbidPrompts(m_frame.page());
3371 ForbidSynchronousLoadsScope forbidSynchronousLoads(m_frame.page());
3372 domWindow->dispatchEvent(beforeUnloadEvent, domWindow->document());
3373 }
3374
3375 if (!beforeUnloadEvent->defaultPrevented())
3376 document->defaultEventHandler(beforeUnloadEvent.get());
3377
3378 if (!shouldAskForNavigationConfirmation(*document, beforeUnloadEvent))
3379 return true;
3380
3381 // If the navigating FrameLoader has already shown a beforeunload confirmation panel for the current navigation attempt,
3382 // this frame is not allowed to cause another one to be shown.
3383 if (frameLoaderBeingNavigated->m_currentNavigationHasShownBeforeUnloadConfirmPanel) {
3384 document->addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::JS, MessageLevel::Error, "Blocked attempt to show multiple beforeunload confirmation dialogs for the same navigation."_s);
3385 return true;
3386 }
3387
3388 // We should only display the beforeunload dialog for an iframe if its SecurityOrigin matches all
3389 // ancestor frame SecurityOrigins up through the navigating FrameLoader.
3390 if (frameLoaderBeingNavigated != this) {
3391 Frame* parentFrame = m_frame.tree().parent();
3392 while (parentFrame) {
3393 Document* parentDocument = parentFrame->document();
3394 if (!parentDocument)
3395 return true;
3396 if (!m_frame.document() || !m_frame.document()->securityOrigin().isSameOriginDomain(parentDocument->securityOrigin())) {
3397 document->addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::JS, MessageLevel::Error, "Blocked attempt to show beforeunload confirmation dialog on behalf of a frame with different security origin. Protocols, domains, and ports must match."_s);
3398 return true;
3399 }
3400
3401 if (&parentFrame->loader() == frameLoaderBeingNavigated)
3402 break;
3403
3404 parentFrame = parentFrame->tree().parent();
3405 }
3406
3407 // The navigatingFrameLoader should always be in our ancestory.
3408 ASSERT(parentFrame);
3409 ASSERT(&parentFrame->loader() == frameLoaderBeingNavigated);
3410 }
3411
3412 frameLoaderBeingNavigated->m_currentNavigationHasShownBeforeUnloadConfirmPanel = true;
3413
3414 String text = document->displayStringModifiedByEncoding(beforeUnloadEvent->returnValue());
3415 return chrome.runBeforeUnloadConfirmPanel(text, m_frame);
3416}

3418void FrameLoader::continueLoadAfterNavigationPolicy(const ResourceRequest& request, FormState* formState, NavigationPolicyDecision navigationPolicyDecision, AllowNavigationToInvalidURL allowNavigationToInvalidURL)
3419{
3420 // If we loaded an alternate page to replace an unreachableURL, we'll get in here with a
3421 // nil policyDataSource because loading the alternate page will have passed
3422 // through this method already, nested; otherwise, policyDataSource should still be set.
3423 ASSERT(m_policyDocumentLoader || !m_provisionalDocumentLoader->unreachableURL().isEmpty());
3424
3425 bool isTargetItem = history().provisionalItem() ? history().provisionalItem()->isTargetItem() : false;
3426
3427 bool urlIsDisallowed = allowNavigationToInvalidURL == AllowNavigationToInvalidURL::No && !request.url().isValid();
3428 bool canContinue = navigationPolicyDecision == NavigationPolicyDecision::ContinueLoad && shouldClose() && !urlIsDisallowed;
3429
3430 if (!canContinue) {
3431 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "continueLoadAfterNavigationPolicy: can't continue loading frame due to the following reasons ("
3432 "allowNavigationToInvalidURL = %d, "
3433 "requestURLIsValid = %d, "
3434 "navigationPolicyDecision = %d)",
3435 static_cast<int>(allowNavigationToInvalidURL),
3436 request.url().isValid(),
3437 static_cast<int>(navigationPolicyDecision));
3438
3439 // If we were waiting for a quick redirect, but the policy delegate decided to ignore it, then we
3440 // need to report that the client redirect was cancelled.
3441 // FIXME: The client should be told about ignored non-quick redirects, too.
3442 if (m_quickRedirectComing)
3443 clientRedirectCancelledOrFinished(NewLoadInProgress::No);
3444
3445 if (navigationPolicyDecision == NavigationPolicyDecision::StopAllLoads) {
3446 stopAllLoaders();
3447 m_checkTimer.stop();
3448 }
3449
3450 setPolicyDocumentLoader(nullptr);
3451 checkCompleted();
3452
3453 if (navigationPolicyDecision != NavigationPolicyDecision::StopAllLoads)
3454 checkLoadComplete();
3455
3456 // If the navigation request came from the back/forward menu, and we punt on it, we have the
3457 // problem that we have optimistically moved the b/f cursor already, so move it back. For sanity,
3458 // we only do this when punting a navigation for the target frame or top-level frame.
3459 if ((isTargetItem || m_frame.isMainFrame()) && isBackForwardLoadType(policyChecker().loadType())) {
3460 if (Page* page = m_frame.page()) {
3461 if (HistoryItem* resetItem = m_frame.mainFrame().loader().history().currentItem())
3462 page->backForward().setCurrentItem(*resetItem);
3463 }
3464 }
3465 return;
3466 }
3467
3468 FrameLoadType type = policyChecker().loadType();
3469 // A new navigation is in progress, so don't clear the history's provisional item.
3470 stopAllLoaders(ClearProvisionalItem::No);
3471
3472 // <rdar://problem/6250856> - In certain circumstances on pages with multiple frames, stopAllLoaders()
3473 // might detach the current FrameLoader, in which case we should bail on this newly defunct load.
3474 if (!m_frame.page()) {
3475 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "continueLoadAfterNavigationPolicy: can't continue loading frame because it became defunct");
3476 return;
3477 }
3478
3479 setProvisionalDocumentLoader(m_policyDocumentLoader.get());
3480 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "continueLoadAfterNavigationPolicy: Setting provisional document loader (m_provisionalDocumentLoader=%p)", m_provisionalDocumentLoader.get());
3481 m_loadType = type;
3482 setState(FrameState::Provisional);
3483
3484 setPolicyDocumentLoader(nullptr);
3485
3486 if (isBackForwardLoadType(type)) {
3487 auto& diagnosticLoggingClient = m_frame.page()->diagnosticLoggingClient();
3488 if (history().provisionalItem() && history().provisionalItem()->isInBackForwardCache()) {
3489 diagnosticLoggingClient.logDiagnosticMessageWithResult(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::backForwardCacheKey(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::retrievalKey(), DiagnosticLoggingResultPass, ShouldSample::Yes);
3490 loadProvisionalItemFromCachedPage();
3491 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "continueLoadAfterNavigationPolicy: can't continue loading frame because it will be loaded from cache");
3492 return;
3493 }
3494 diagnosticLoggingClient.logDiagnosticMessageWithResult(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::backForwardCacheKey(), DiagnosticLoggingKeys::retrievalKey(), DiagnosticLoggingResultFail, ShouldSample::Yes);
3495 }
3496
3497 CompletionHandler<void()> completionHandler = [this, protectedFrame = makeRef(m_frame)] () mutable {
3498 if (!m_provisionalDocumentLoader) {
3499 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "continueLoadAfterNavigationPolicy (completionHandler): Frame load canceled - no provisional document loader before prepareForLoadStart");
3500 return;
3501 }
3502
3503 prepareForLoadStart();
3504
3505 // The load might be cancelled inside of prepareForLoadStart(), nulling out the m_provisionalDocumentLoader,
3506 // so we need to null check it again.
3507 if (!m_provisionalDocumentLoader) {
3508 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "continueLoadAfterNavigationPolicy (completionHandler): Frame load canceled - no provisional document loader after prepareForLoadStart");
3509 return;
3510 }
3511
3512 DocumentLoader* activeDocLoader = activeDocumentLoader();
3513 if (activeDocLoader && activeDocLoader->isLoadingMainResource()) {
3514 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "continueLoadAfterNavigationPolicy (completionHandler): Main frame already being loaded");
3515 return;
3516 }
3517
3518 m_loadingFromCachedPage = false;
3519
3520 m_provisionalDocumentLoader->startLoadingMainResource();
3521 };
3522
3523 if (!formState) {
3524 completionHandler();
3525 return;
3526 }
3527
3528 m_client->dispatchWillSubmitForm(*formState, WTFMove(completionHandler));
3529}

3581void FrameLoader::loadedResourceFromMemoryCache(CachedResource& resource, ResourceRequest& newRequest, ResourceError& error)
3582{
3583 Page* page = m_frame.page();
3584 if (!page)
3585 return;
3586
3587 if (!resource.shouldSendResourceLoadCallbacks() || m_documentLoader->haveToldClientAboutLoad(resource.url().string()))
3588 return;
3589
3590 // Main resource delegate messages are synthesized in MainResourceLoader, so we must not send them here.
3591 if (resource.type() == CachedResource::Type::MainResource)
3592 return;
3593
3594 if (!page->areMemoryCacheClientCallsEnabled()) {
3595 InspectorInstrumentation::didLoadResourceFromMemoryCache(*page, m_documentLoader.get(), &resource);
3596 m_documentLoader->recordMemoryCacheLoadForFutureClientNotification(resource.resourceRequest());
3597 m_documentLoader->didTellClientAboutLoad(resource.url().string());
3598 return;
3599 }
3600
3601 if (m_client->dispatchDidLoadResourceFromMemoryCache(m_documentLoader.get(), newRequest, resource.response(), resource.encodedSize())) {
3602 InspectorInstrumentation::didLoadResourceFromMemoryCache(*page, m_documentLoader.get(), &resource);
3603 m_documentLoader->didTellClientAboutLoad(resource.url().string());
3604 return;
3605 }
3606
3607 unsigned long identifier;
3608 requestFromDelegate(newRequest, identifier, error);
3609
3610 ResourceResponse response = resource.response();
3611 response.setSource(ResourceResponse::Source::MemoryCache);

3624bool FrameLoader::shouldInterruptLoadForXFrameOptions(const String& content, const URL& url, unsigned long requestIdentifier)
3625{
3626 Frame& topFrame = m_frame.tree().top();
3627 if (&m_frame == &topFrame)
3628 return false;
3629
3630 XFrameOptionsDisposition disposition = parseXFrameOptionsHeader(content);
3631
3632 switch (disposition) {
3633 case XFrameOptionsDisposition::SameOrigin: {
3634 auto origin = SecurityOrigin::create(url);
3635 if (!origin->isSameSchemeHostPort(topFrame.document()->securityOrigin()))
3636 return true;
3637 for (Frame* frame = m_frame.tree().parent(); frame; frame = frame->tree().parent()) {
3638 if (!origin->isSameSchemeHostPort(frame->document()->securityOrigin()))
3639 return true;
3640 }
3641 return false;
3642 }
3643 case XFrameOptionsDisposition::Deny:
3644 return true;
3645 case XFrameOptionsDisposition::AllowAll:
3646 return false;
3647 case XFrameOptionsDisposition::Conflict:
3648 m_frame.document()->addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::JS, MessageLevel::Error, "Multiple 'X-Frame-Options' headers with conflicting values ('" + content + "') encountered when loading '" + url.stringCenterEllipsizedToLength() + "'. Falling back to 'DENY'.", requestIdentifier);
3649 return true;
3650 case XFrameOptionsDisposition::Invalid:
3651 m_frame.document()->addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::JS, MessageLevel::Error, "Invalid 'X-Frame-Options' header encountered when loading '" + url.stringCenterEllipsizedToLength() + "': '" + content + "' is not a recognized directive. The header will be ignored.", requestIdentifier);
3652 return false;
3653 case XFrameOptionsDisposition::None:
3654 return false;
3655 }
3656 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3657 return false;
3658}

3711void FrameLoader::loadSameDocumentItem(HistoryItem& item)

3732// FIXME: This function should really be split into a couple pieces, some of
3733// which should be methods of HistoryController and some of which should be
3734// methods of FrameLoader.
3735void FrameLoader::loadDifferentDocumentItem(HistoryItem& item, HistoryItem* fromItem, FrameLoadType loadType, FormSubmissionCacheLoadPolicy cacheLoadPolicy, ShouldTreatAsContinuingLoad shouldTreatAsContinuingLoad)
3736{
3737 FRAMELOADER_RELEASE_LOG(ResourceLoading, "loadDifferentDocumentItem: frame load started");
3738
3739 Ref<Frame> protectedFrame(m_frame);
3740
3741 // History items should not be reported to the parent.
3742 m_shouldReportResourceTimingToParentFrame = false;
3743
3744 // Remember this item so we can traverse any child items as child frames load
3745 history().setProvisionalItem(&item);
3746
3747 auto initiatedByMainFrame = InitiatedByMainFrame::Unknown;
3748
3749 SetForScope<LoadContinuingState> continuingLoadGuard(m_currentLoadContinuingState, shouldTreatAsContinuingLoad == ShouldTreatAsContinuingLoad::Yes ? LoadContinuingState::ContinuingWithHistoryItem : LoadContinuingState::NotContinuing);
3750
3751 if (CachedPage* cachedPage = BackForwardCache::singleton().get(item, m_frame.page())) {
3752 auto documentLoader = cachedPage->documentLoader();
3753 m_client->updateCachedDocumentLoader(*documentLoader);
3754
3755 auto action = NavigationAction { *m_frame.document(), documentLoader->request(), initiatedByMainFrame, loadType, false };
3756 action.setTargetBackForwardItem(item);
3757 action.setSourceBackForwardItem(fromItem);
3758 documentLoader->setTriggeringAction(WTFMove(action));
3759
3760 documentLoader->setLastCheckedRequest(ResourceRequest());
3761 loadWithDocumentLoader(documentLoader, loadType, { }, AllowNavigationToInvalidURL::Yes);
3762 return;
3763 }
3764
3765 URL itemURL = item.url();
3766 URL itemOriginalURL = item.originalURL();
3767 URL currentURL;
3768 if (documentLoader())
3769 currentURL = documentLoader()->url();
3770 RefPtr<FormData> formData = item.formData();
3771
3772 ResourceRequest request(itemURL);
3773
3774 if (!item.referrer().isNull())
3775 request.setHTTPReferrer(item.referrer());
3776
3777 ShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy = shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToApply(m_frame, initiatedByMainFrame, item.shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy());
3778 bool isFormSubmission = false;
3779 Event* event = nullptr;
3780
3781 // If this was a repost that failed the page cache, we might try to repost the form.
3782 NavigationAction action;
3783 if (formData) {
3784 request.setHTTPMethod("POST");
3785 request.setHTTPBody(WTFMove(formData));
3786 request.setHTTPContentType(item.formContentType());
3787 auto securityOrigin = SecurityOrigin::createFromString(item.referrer());
3788 addHTTPOriginIfNeeded(request, securityOrigin->toString());
3789
3790 updateRequestAndAddExtraFields(request, IsMainResource::Yes, loadType);
3791
3792 // FIXME: Slight hack to test if the NSURL cache contains the page we're going to.
3793 // We want to know this before talking to the policy delegate, since it affects whether
3794 // we show the DoYouReallyWantToRepost nag.
3795 //
3796 // This trick has a small bug (3123893) where we might find a cache hit, but then
3797 // have the item vanish when we try to use it in the ensuing nav. This should be
3798 // extremely rare, but in that case the user will get an error on the navigation.
3799
3800 if (cacheLoadPolicy == MayAttemptCacheOnlyLoadForFormSubmissionItem) {
3801 request.setCachePolicy(ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReturnCacheDataDontLoad);
3802 action = { *m_frame.document(), request, initiatedByMainFrame, loadType, isFormSubmission, event, shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy };
3803 } else {
3804 request.setCachePolicy(ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReturnCacheDataElseLoad);
3805 action = { *m_frame.document(), request, initiatedByMainFrame, NavigationType::FormResubmitted, shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy, event };
3806 }
3807 } else {
3808 switch (loadType) {
3809 case FrameLoadType::Reload:
3810 case FrameLoadType::ReloadFromOrigin:
3811 case FrameLoadType::ReloadExpiredOnly:
3812 request.setCachePolicy(ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData);
3813 break;
3814 case FrameLoadType::Back:
3815 case FrameLoadType::Forward:
3816 case FrameLoadType::IndexedBackForward: {
3817#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
3818 bool allowStaleData = true;
3819#else
3820 bool allowStaleData = !item.wasRestoredFromSession();
3821#endif
3822 if (allowStaleData)
3823 request.setCachePolicy(ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReturnCacheDataElseLoad);
3824 item.setWasRestoredFromSession(false);
3825 break;
3826 }
3827 case FrameLoadType::Standard:
3828 case FrameLoadType::RedirectWithLockedBackForwardList:
3829 break;
3830 case FrameLoadType::Same:
3831 case FrameLoadType::Replace:
3832 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3833 }
3834
3835 updateRequestAndAddExtraFields(request, IsMainResource::Yes, loadType);
3836
3837 ResourceRequest requestForOriginalURL(request);
3838 requestForOriginalURL.setURL(itemOriginalURL);
3839 action = { *m_frame.document(), requestForOriginalURL, initiatedByMainFrame, loadType, isFormSubmission, event, shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy };
3840 }
3841
3842 action.setTargetBackForwardItem(item);
3843 action.setSourceBackForwardItem(fromItem);
3844
3845 loadWithNavigationAction(request, WTFMove(action), loadType, { }, AllowNavigationToInvalidURL::Yes);
3846}

3848// Loads content into this frame, as specified by history item
3849void FrameLoader::loadItem(HistoryItem& item, HistoryItem* fromItem, FrameLoadType loadType, ShouldTreatAsContinuingLoad shouldTreatAsContinuingLoad)
3850{
3851 m_requestedHistoryItem = &item;
3852 HistoryItem* currentItem = history().currentItem();
3853 bool sameDocumentNavigation = currentItem && item.shouldDoSameDocumentNavigationTo(*currentItem);
3854
3855 // If we're continuing this history navigation in a new process, then doing a same document navigation never makes sense.
3856 ASSERT(!sameDocumentNavigation || shouldTreatAsContinuingLoad == ShouldTreatAsContinuingLoad::No);
3857
3858 if (sameDocumentNavigation)
3859 loadSameDocumentItem(item);
3860 else
3861 loadDifferentDocumentItem(item, fromItem, loadType, MayAttemptCacheOnlyLoadForFormSubmissionItem, shouldTreatAsContinuingLoad);
3862}

3864void FrameLoader::retryAfterFailedCacheOnlyMainResourceLoad()
3865{
3866 ASSERT(m_state == FrameState::Provisional);
3867 ASSERT(!m_loadingFromCachedPage);
3868 ASSERT(history().provisionalItem());
3869 ASSERT(history().provisionalItem()->formData());
3870 ASSERT(history().provisionalItem() == m_requestedHistoryItem.get());

4066RefPtr<Frame> createWindow(Frame& openerFrame, Frame& lookupFrame, FrameLoadRequest&& request, const WindowFeatures& features, bool& created)
4067{
4068 ASSERT(!features.dialog || request.frameName().isEmpty());
4069 ASSERT(request.resourceRequest().httpMethod() == "GET");
4070
4071 created = false;
4072
4073 // FIXME: Provide line number information with respect to the opener's document.
4074 if (request.resourceRequest().url().protocolIsJavaScript() && !openerFrame.document()->contentSecurityPolicy()->allowJavaScriptURLs(openerFrame.document()->url().string(), { }))
4075 return nullptr;
4076
4077 if (!request.frameName().isEmpty() && !equalIgnoringASCIICase(request.frameName(), "_blank")) {
4078 if (RefPtr<Frame> frame = lookupFrame.loader().findFrameForNavigation(request.frameName(), openerFrame.document())) {
4079 if (!equalIgnoringASCIICase(request.frameName(), "_self")) {
4080 if (Page* page = frame->page())
4081 page->chrome().focus();
4082 }
4083 return frame;
4084 }
4085 }
4086
4087 // Sandboxed frames cannot open new auxiliary browsing contexts.
4088 if (isDocumentSandboxed(openerFrame, SandboxPopups)) {
4089 // FIXME: This message should be moved off the console once a solution to https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=103274 exists.
4090 openerFrame.document()->addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, "Blocked opening '" + request.resourceRequest().url().stringCenterEllipsizedToLength() + "' in a new window because the request was made in a sandboxed frame whose 'allow-popups' permission is not set.");
4091 return nullptr;
4092 }
4093
4094 // FIXME: Setting the referrer should be the caller's responsibility.
4095 String referrer = SecurityPolicy::generateReferrerHeader(openerFrame.document()->referrerPolicy(), request.resourceRequest().url(), openerFrame.loader().outgoingReferrer());
4096 if (!referrer.isEmpty())
4097 request.resourceRequest().setHTTPReferrer(referrer);
4098 FrameLoader::addSameSiteInfoToRequestIfNeeded(request.resourceRequest(), openerFrame.document());
4099
4100 Page* oldPage = openerFrame.page();
4101 if (!oldPage)
4102 return nullptr;
4103
4104 ShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy = shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToApply(openerFrame, request);
4105 NavigationAction action { request.requester(), request.resourceRequest(), request.initiatedByMainFrame(), NavigationType::Other, shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy };
4106 Page* page = oldPage->chrome().createWindow(openerFrame, features, action);
4107 if (!page)
4108 return nullptr;
4109
4110 RefPtr<Frame> frame = &page->mainFrame();
4111
4112 if (isDocumentSandboxed(openerFrame, SandboxPropagatesToAuxiliaryBrowsingContexts))
4113 frame->loader().forceSandboxFlags(openerFrame.document()->sandboxFlags());
4114
4115 if (!equalIgnoringASCIICase(request.frameName(), "_blank"))
4116 frame->tree().setName(request.frameName());
4117
4118 page->chrome().setToolbarsVisible(features.toolBarVisible || features.locationBarVisible);
4119
4120 if (!frame->page())
4121 return nullptr;
4122 page->chrome().setStatusbarVisible(features.statusBarVisible);
4123
4124 if (!frame->page())
4125 return nullptr;
4126 page->chrome().setScrollbarsVisible(features.scrollbarsVisible);
4127
4128 if (!frame->page())
4129 return nullptr;
4130 page->chrome().setMenubarVisible(features.menuBarVisible);
4131
4132 if (!frame->page())
4133 return nullptr;
4134 page->chrome().setResizable(features.resizable);
4135
4136 // 'x' and 'y' specify the location of the window, while 'width' and 'height'
4137 // specify the size of the viewport. We can only resize the window, so adjust
4138 // for the difference between the window size and the viewport size.
4139
4140 // FIXME: We should reconcile the initialization of viewport arguments between iOS and non-IOS.
4141#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
4142 FloatSize viewportSize = page->chrome().pageRect().size();
4143 FloatRect windowRect = page->chrome().windowRect();
4144 if (features.x)
4145 windowRect.setX(*features.x);
4146 if (features.y)
4147 windowRect.setY(*features.y);
4148 // Zero width and height mean using default size, not minimum one.
4149 if (features.width && *features.width)
4150 windowRect.setWidth(*features.width + (windowRect.width() - viewportSize.width()));
4151 if (features.height && *features.height)
4152 windowRect.setHeight(*features.height + (windowRect.height() - viewportSize.height()));
4153
4154#if PLATFORM(GTK)
4155 FloatRect oldWindowRect = oldPage->chrome().windowRect();
4156 // Use the size of the previous window if there is no default size.
4157 if (!windowRect.width())
4158 windowRect.setWidth(oldWindowRect.width());
4159 if (!windowRect.height())
4160 windowRect.setHeight(oldWindowRect.height());
4161#endif
4162
4163 // Ensure non-NaN values, minimum size as well as being within valid screen area.
4164 FloatRect newWindowRect = DOMWindow::adjustWindowRect(*page, windowRect);
4165
4166 if (!frame->page())
4167 return nullptr;
4168 page->chrome().setWindowRect(newWindowRect);
4169#else
4170 // On iOS, width and height refer to the viewport dimensions.
4171 ViewportArguments arguments;
4172 // Zero width and height mean using default size, not minimum one.
4173 if (features.width && *features.width)
4174 arguments.width = *features.width;
4175 if (features.height && *features.height)
4176 arguments.height = *features.height;
4177 frame->setViewportArguments(arguments);
4178#endif
4179
4180 if (!frame->page())
4181 return nullptr;
4182 page->chrome().show();
4183
4184 created = true;
4185 return frame;
4186}
